enter\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4 offset-lg-2\">\r\n    <img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-diane-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"staff-diane\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3991 rounded-circle\" />\r\n    <h3>Diane Thigpen<br /> <small>Expanded Duty Dental Assistant</small></h3>\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/meet-our-staff/diane-thigpen\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Read More <i class=\"fa fa-angle-right\"></i></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/lisa-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"lisa-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4320 rounded-circle\" />\r\n    <h3>Lisa Johnson<br /> <small>Certified Dental Assistant</small></h3>\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/meet-our-staff/lisa-j-johnson/\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Read More <i class=\"fa fa-angle-right\"></i></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Meet Our Staff','','publish','closed','closed','','meet-our-staff','','','2017-10-18 14:28:17','2017-10-18 14:28:17','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=3999',0,'page','',0),(4002,1001007,'2016-03-21 23:35:04','2016-03-21 23:35:04','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-lorrie.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3995\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-lorrie-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"staff-lorrie\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3995 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Lorrie joined our team in 2008 as our Financial Coordinator. She files insurance as a courtesy to our patients and works with insurance companies to get the most out of your dental benefits.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Lorrie received her diploma in business from Horry Georgetown Technical College and is x-ray certified. She lives in Galivants Ferry with her husband, John. Her daughter, Victoria, attends Clemson University and is a Computer Science major.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Lorrie Watts','','publish','closed','closed','','lorrie-watts','','','2017-04-07 15:04:10','2017-04-07 15:04:10','',3999,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4002',0,'page','',0),(4008,1001007,'2016-03-21 23:37:29','2016-03-21 23:37:29','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-anna.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3990\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-anna-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"staff-anna\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3990 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Anna began her dental hygiene career at Blevins Dentistry upon completion of her degree from Florence Darlington Technical College in 2012. She helps our patients keep their smiles bright and clean and specializes in periodontal therapy.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Anna is certified to use anesthesia to provide our patients with added comfort. Anna enjoys spending time with her husband and family.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Anna Rogers, RDH','','publish','closed','closed','','anna-rogers-rdh','','','2017-04-07 15:04:39','2017-04-07 15:04:39','',3999,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4008',0,'page','',0),(4010,1001007,'2016-03-21 23:38:13','2016-03-21 23:38:13','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-megan.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3996\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-megan-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"staff-megan\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3996 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Megan joined the Blevins team in 2014 as a registered dental hygienist. She graduated from Florence-Darlington Technical College in 2010 and is licensed to administer anesthesia for added patient comfort.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Megan is adept at treating periodontal disease, counseling on preventative care and encouraging our patients to practice home care habits that improve their whole body health and quality of life.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Megan enjoys gardening, tending to her chickens and various other pets, and spending time with her husband.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Megan Snipes, RDH','','publish','closed','closed','','megan-snipes-rdh','','','2017-04-07 15:03:39','2017-04-07 15:03:39','',3999,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4010',0,'page','',0),(4014,1001007,'2016-03-21 23:40:09','2016-03-21 23:40:09','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-diane.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3991\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/staff-diane-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"staff-diane\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3991 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Diane joined Blevins Dentistry in 2006 as a Certified and Expanded Duty Dental Assistant. She has been making patients smile in the dental field for over thirty years. Diane assists Dr. Blevins with many procedures, and her forte is in the area Single Visit Dentistry utilizing CEREC crowns and bridges.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>One of the reasons she enjoys working at Blevins Dentistry is because she is free to share her love for the Lord with patients. Outside the office, she enjoys bike riding, fishing, and spending time with her dog, Willow. Diane and her husband, Frank, live in Marion.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Diane Thigpen','','publish','closed','closed','','diane-thigpen','','','2017-04-07 15:06:57','2017-04-07 15:06:57','',3999,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4014',0,'page','',0),(4021,1001007,'2016-03-22 00:38:59','2016-03-22 00:38:59','','slide2','','inherit','open','closed','','slide2-2','','','2016-03-22 00:40:56','2016-03-22 00:40:56','',3988,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/slide2-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4029,1001007,'2016-03-23 21:19:01','2016-03-23 21:19:01','','slide3-new','','inherit','open','closed','','slide3-new','','','2016-03-23 21:19:01','2016-03-23 21:19:01','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/slide3-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4031,1001007,'2016-03-29 19:09:43','2016-03-29 19:09:43','','blevins-logo2','','inherit','open','closed','','blevins-logo2','','','2016-03-29 19:09:43','2016-03-29 19:09:43','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/blevins-logo2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4032,1001007,'2016-03-29 19:23:57','2016-03-29 19:23:57','','slide4-new','','inherit','open','closed','','slide4-new','','','2016-03-29 19:23:57','2016-03-29 19:23:57','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/slide4-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4036,1001007,'2016-03-29 19:47:58','2016-03-29 19:47:58','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4037\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"dental oral exam Mullins, SC\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4037 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Seeing Dr. Blevins and our experienced dental hygienists for a routine oral health examination is critical to maintaining your oral health and well-being. After all, <strong>the first line of defense against serious health issues is prevention and early detection.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n    <p>When you visit Blevins Dentistry for your routine dental exams every 4-6 months, we will be able to keep a close watch on your oral health, which is a major factor in preventing serious and costly dental problems down the road.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Here are just a few services we provide as part of a thorough dental exam:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Oral cancer screening</li>\r\n	<li>Visual examinations to check for tooth decay, gum erosion, or bone loss.</li> \r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/digital-radiography/\" target=\"_blank\">Diagnostic x-rays</a> to look for tumors, cysts, and other problems that are not always seen with the naked eye.</li> \r\n	<li>Evaluation of dental work you’ve had done in the past (such as cosmetic, restorative, or orthodontics) to see if everything is still functioning correctly.</li> \r\n        <li>We also do a thorough periodontal disease evaluation. <a href=\"https://www.perio.org/newsroom/periodontal-disease-fact-sheet\" target=\"_blank\">According to the CDC</a>, approximately half of adults over age 30 have periodontal disease. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Don’t take a risk with your dental health. Contact Blevins Dentistry today to schedule your comprehensive dental examination.</p> ','Thorough Dental Exams','','publish','closed','closed','','thorough-dental-exams','','','2017-04-06 20:52:08','2017-04-06 20:52:08','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4036',0,'page','',0),(4037,1001007,'2016-03-29 19:47:45','2016-03-29 19:47:45','','doctor-patient-square','','inherit','open','closed','','doctor-patient-square','','','2016-03-29 19:47:45','2016-03-29 19:47:45','',4036,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4048,1001007,'2016-03-29 19:53:08','2016-03-29 19:53:08','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cleanings-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4054\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cleanings-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"cleanings-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4054 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>While we certainly recommend you visiting our office at least twice a year for a professional cleaning, <strong>if it has been a long time since your last cleaning, don’t worry; there’s no judgment at Blevins Dentistry.</strong></p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Our goal with professional cleanings isn’t to evaluate your past dental history; rather, it’s to give your teeth a thorough cleaning and examination, putting you on the path to better overall oral health and wellness moving forward.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-10 offset-lg-1\">\r\n    <h3>Here are just a few things our dental hygienists will do at your appointment to ensure you leave our office with a happier, healthier smile:</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>• Removal of plaque and tarter from your teeth and gums. Over time plaque and tarter can form from food, saliva, and bacteria. It’s important to keep a close eye on them, as they can lead to more severe dental problems down the road if not taken care of appropriately.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>• Polishing and removing stubborn stains from teeth. While not all enamel stains can be removed during a professional cleaning, a professional hygienist can polish your teeth and improve your appearance drastically. Plus, your mouth will feel very clean after your visit!</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>• Fluoride treatments for children and teens to strengthen tooth enamel and reduce the risk of tooth decay.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Depending on your unique needs, we may also recommend x-rays, as well as discuss nutrition with you in order to ensure your mouth is healthy for years to come.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Professional Cleanings','','publish','closed','closed','','professional-cleanings','','','2017-04-07 14:46:53','2017-04-07 14:46:53','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4048',0,'page','',0),(4054,1001007,'2016-03-29 19:57:08','2016-03-29 19:57:08','','cleanings-square','','inherit','open','closed','','cleanings-square','','','2016-03-29 19:57:08','2016-03-29 19:57:08','',4048,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cleanings-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4059,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:00:50','2016-03-29 20:00:50','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4062\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"gum-disease-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4062 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Periodontal disease can affect one tooth or many teeth. It begins when the bacteria in plaque (the sticky, colorless film that constantly forms on your teeth) causes the gums to become inflamed.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>If you think you may have gum disease or have been told that you have periodontal disease, it’s important to take proper care of your oral health in order to prevent your condition from worsening.</strong></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>Here are a few tips:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Brush your teeth with a toothpaste designed to fight gum disease.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure to floss every day, as plaque can build up quickly in the crevices between teeth.</li> \r\n	<li>Use mouthwash after you brush to freshen your breath and kill bacteria.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you think you may be suffering from gingivitis or a more advanced form of periodontal disease, it’s important to seek treatment immediately because treatment becomes more complicated as your condition worsens.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>If you are in Mullins, Florence, Myrtle Beach, or any of the surrounding areas, we encourage you to contact our office today to schedule your periodontal disease evaluation.</p>','Gum Disease Care','','publish','closed','closed','','gum-disease-care','','','2017-04-06 20:57:37','2017-04-06 20:57:37','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4059',0,'page','',0),(4062,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:02:27','2016-03-29 20:02:27','','gum-disease-square','','inherit','open','closed','','gum-disease-square','','','2016-03-29 20:02:27','2016-03-29 20:02:27','',4059,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4067,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:25:32','2016-03-29 20:25:32','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-xrays-square-2.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4071\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-xrays-square-2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"dental-xrays-square-2\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4071 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Overexposure to radiation is a concern that many patients express in regards to x-rays. At Blevins Dentistry, we understand these concerns, which is why we offer digital radiography to all of our patients as an alternative to traditional x-rays.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p><strong>In fact, digital x-rays actually expose you to less radiation than an average flight on a commercial airline.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n    <p>So if you’ve avoided the dentist because of x-rays, our safe, effective digital x-ray technology should put your mind at ease. If you’d like to schedule a dental appointment, please give our office a call or contact us today.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>  ','Digital Radiography','','publish','closed','closed','','digital-radiography','','','2017-04-06 20:59:41','2017-04-06 20:59:41','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4067',0,'page','',0),(4071,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:27:19','2016-03-29 20:27:19','','dental-xrays-square-2','','inherit','open','closed','','dental-xrays-square-2','','','2016-03-29 20:27:19','2016-03-29 20:27:19','',4067,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-xrays-square-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4074,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:29:45','2016-03-29 20:29:45','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-5\">\r\n    <p class=\"lead\">A crown is typically used to restore a damaged tooth back to its natural look, and a bridge is simply a series of crowns that are used to restore multiple teeth or to “bridge the gap” between missing teeth.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-7 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5brsnWhN_lQ\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/5brsnWhN_lQ/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>Options to Restore Teeth Lost Due to Decay</em></small></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>What makes dental crowns and bridges at Blevins Dentistry different from many other dental providers is that <strong>we turn the dental crown process into a single, one-day event</strong>, meaning that you can receive your dental crown and get on with your life.</p> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cerec-omnicam-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4079\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cerec-omnicam-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"cerec-omnicam-square\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4079 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>How do we do it?</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>At Blevins Dentistry, we have a CEREC® crowns machine that enables us to take a digital impression of your teeth at our office, which removes the need for manual impressions and having to get an off-site dental lab involved in the process.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>After the CEREC® CAD/CAM system takes a 3D digital impression of your teeth, Dr. Blevins is then able to use the CEREC® milling process to provide you with a perfect ceramic dental crown or a bridge that fits perfectly. The end result is a complete restoration that improves your smile, self-confidence, and overall dental health.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>If you would like to learn more about single visit crowns and bridges from Blevins Dentistry, give our office a call today or contact us to schedule your appointment. We look forward to seeing you in our dental practice soon.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> ','Crowns and Bridges','','publish','closed','closed','','crowns-and-bridges','','','2017-09-27 17:51:20','2017-09-27 17:51:20','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4074',0,'page','',0),(4075,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:29:33','2016-03-29 20:29:33','','crowns-square','','inherit','open','closed','','crowns-square-2','','','2016-03-29 20:29:33','2016-03-29 20:29:33','',4074,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crowns-square-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4079,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:32:51','2016-03-29 20:32:51','','cerec-omnicam-square','','inherit','open','closed','','cerec-omnicam-square','','','2016-03-29 20:32:51','2016-03-29 20:32:51','',4074,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cerec-omnicam-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4082,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:35:37','2016-03-29 20:35:37','<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-7 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5brsnWhN_lQ\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/5brsnWhN_lQ/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>Options to Restore Teeth Lost Due to Decay</em></small></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-5\">\r\n    <p>When patients talk about a snap-in denture, what they are likely referring to is an overdenture, which is a special type of denture that basically “snaps in place” over <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/\">dental implants</a>.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>While snap-in or snap-on dentures are an incredible treatment for patients who are missing teeth, it’s important to remember that they are not the same as a permanent crown or dental bridge.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-10 offset-lg-1\">\r\n    <img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dentures-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"snap in dentures with great fit\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4085 rounded-circle\" />\r\n\r\n    <p>In other words, you have to take them out on a consistent basis and clean them.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>While every person’s situation is unique, snap-in dentures typically require 2-4 dental implants on the bottom and 4-8 implants on the top. The more implants, the more stable the denture will be.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>At <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com\">Blevins Dentistry</a>, we use only the highest quality materials and work with the finest dental lab in order to make natural-looking dentures that will improve your smile and self-confidence. Dentures can also help patients who are suffering from facial sagging due to the loss of teeth.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>If you’re in the Myrtle Beach, Mullins, Florence or surrounding area we encourage you to contact us today to schedule your dentures consultation.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Snap-in Dentures','','publish','closed','closed','','snap-in-dentures','','','2017-09-27 17:50:33','2017-09-27 17:50:33','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4082',0,'page','',0),(4085,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:39:48','2016-03-29 20:39:48','','dentures-square','','inherit','open','closed','','dentures-square','','','2016-03-29 20:39:48','2016-03-29 20:39:48','',4082,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dentures-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4087,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:41:43','2016-03-29 20:41:43','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>A tooth-colored composite filling is used to fix cavities and restore decaying teeth. Typically, we will place the composite filling in layers, use a special dental-grade light to harden each layer appropriately.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>After the material is in place, Dr. Blevins will use his skills to perfectly shape the filling to fit your tooth and also match the shade of your teeth perfectly. This process provides an effective restorative and cosmetic outcome for patients who have a decaying tooth.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>If you think it’s time for a filling, we encourage you to contact our dental office today to schedule your complete oral health examination.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fillings-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4089\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fillings-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"fillings-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4089 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Tooth Colored Fillings','','publish','closed','closed','','tooth-colored-fillings','','','2017-04-06 19:48:52','2017-04-06 19:48:52','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4087',0,'page','',0),(4089,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:42:30','2016-03-29 20:42:30','','fillings-square','','inherit','open','closed','','fillings-square','','','2016-03-29 20:42:30','2016-03-29 20:42:30','',4087,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fillings-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4091,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:44:07','2016-03-29 20:44:07','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3969\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"box1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3969 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>The cosmetic bonding process is similar to tooth-colored fillings, but has a wider application and may be used to:</p>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Repair teeth that are slightly chipped or cracked</li>\r\n	<li>Close small spaces between teeth</li>\r\n	<li>Change the shape of your teeth or make them appear visibly longer</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <p>While some cases require more involved processes, such as veneers and crowns in a single day, some patients only need the convenient and less expensive option of bonding.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, unlike dental crowns or veneers, bonding typically requires minimal removal of enamel and does not usually require sedation.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>While cosmetic dental bonding is an effective solution for minor dental repairs, it should not be used in cases where a significant amount of cosmetic restoration is required. Dental bonding does not last as long as more permanent solutions, such as dental crowns or porcelain veneers.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>If you’re looking to improve your smile with cosmetic dentistry, it\'s best to sit down face to face with Dr. Blevins to discuss your options, as he can recommend which procedure/procedures would help you achieve your goals.</p>','Cosmetic Bonding','','publish','closed','closed','','cosmetic-bonding','','','2017-04-06 21:09:28','2017-04-06 21:09:28','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4091',0,'page','',0),(4095,1001007,'2016-03-29 20:49:18','2016-03-29 20:49:18','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4098\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"full mouth reconstruction Mullins, SC\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4098 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>In most cases, people who require a full mouth reconstruction have either experienced some form of trauma or neglected their oral health for some time. However, with a full mouth rehabilitation from Dr. Blevins, you can improve your smile, oral health, and self-confidence.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>What’s involved in a full mouth rehabilitation?</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>The first step of the full mouth construction process is to evaluate your teeth and gums, which will determine the procedures needed to achieve desired results. <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/\" target=\"_blank\">Dental implants</a> with <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/crowns-and-bridges/\" target=\"_blank\">crowns, bridges</a>, or <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/single-visit-veneers/\" target=\"_blank\">porcelain veneers</a> are typically used as part of the reconstruction process.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>In the event that Dr. Blevins finds evidence of <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/periodontics/\" target=\"_blank\">periodontal disease</a> (an advanced form of gum disease affecting half of all adults in the U.S.), scaling or root planing may be required. In some cases, bone grafts or soft tissue grafting may be required to restore your dental health and strengthen your jaw to support a dental implant restoration.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Last but not least, your bite alignment will be checked to ensure that you aren’t suffering from temporomandibular joint disorder (commonly referred to as TMJ disorder or TMD).</p> \r\n\r\n<p>If you think you may be a candidate for a full mouth restoration, we encourage you to contact our office today to schedule your consultation. Dr. Blevins is one of the most accomplished dentists in South Carolina, and routinely sees cosmetic dentistry patients from Myrtle Beach, Florence, and the surrounding areas.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>You don’t have to live with a smile that doesn’t make you happy. Contact our office here to see how we can help you achieve the best smile you’ve ever had!</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after9.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after9-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after9\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4328\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after10.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after10-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after10\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4329\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after13.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after13-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after13\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4332\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after12.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after12-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after12\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4331\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6 offset-lg-3\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after11.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after11-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after11\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4330\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Full Mouth Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','full-mouth-rehab','','','2017-04-06 21:24:16','2017-04-06 21:24:16','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4095',0,'page','',0),(4098,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:14:41','2016-03-29 21:14:41','','smiling-woman-square','','inherit','open','closed','','smiling-woman-square-2','','','2016-03-29 21:14:41','2016-03-29 21:14:41','',4095,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4100,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:22:42','2016-03-29 21:22:42','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/whitening-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4102\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/whitening-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"teeth whitening mullins, sc\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4102 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>If so, professional teeth whitening from <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com\">Blevins Dentistry</a> is just what you need. Whether you’re looking for a dental-grade teeth whitening treatment that you can administer yourself at home, or prefer an in-office treatment, we have options to meet your needs.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Before any teeth whitening treatment is recommended, <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins/\">Dr. Blevins</a> will meet with you during your appointment to ensure that you are a candidate for teeth whitening. If you are, then based on your wants and needs you’ll choose between Zoom!® take home whitening and Opalescence® Boost in-office whitening.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Zoom!® At home whitening treatment</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>For patients who are looking for a simple, effective solution they can use at home, Zoom!® is ideal. Here is how the Zoom!® Whitening system from Blevins Dentistry works:</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Dr. Blevins will provide you with a set of fabricated tooth whitening trays that are custom fitted to your mouth. In addition, you’ll receive a safe, powerful teeth whitening gel.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Dr. Blevins will also talk with you about how to use the trays properly, including how to ensure the whitening gel makes contact with only your teeth and not your gums (which could lead to increased sensitivity).</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>After the procedure is complete (over a period of a few weeks), your teeth will be whiter, and you’ll be able to evaluate whether or not further whitening is needed.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/zoom-whitening-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4107\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/zoom-whitening-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"zoom teeth whitening\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4107 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Boost in-office teeth whitening</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For our patients who prefer an in-office whitening solution, we offer Boost whitening, a safe, powerful whitening system that can give you incredible results in just two dental visits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Here’s how Boost whitening works:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Boost whitening is chemically activated, which means no hot, uncomfortable lights are necessary.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Your dentist will apply your treatment as needed (depending on the severity of your tooth stains and the shade you are looking to achieve).</p> \r\n\r\n<p>In some cases, a second follow-up treatment is recommended, but Dr. Blevins will discuss this up front with you so there are no surprises when it comes to the cost or time commitment required.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>If you live in or around the Mullins, Myrtle Beach, or Florence areas and are looking to brighten your smile with professional teeth whitening, give our office a call today.</p>','Teeth Whitening','','publish','closed','closed','','teeth-whitening','','','2017-04-06 21:13:52','2017-04-06 21:13:52','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4100',0,'page','',0),(4102,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:23:39','2016-03-29 21:23:39','','whitening-square','','inherit','open','closed','','whitening-square','','','2016-03-29 21:23:39','2016-03-29 21:23:39','',4100,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/whitening-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4107,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:26:46','2016-03-29 21:26:46','','zoom-whitening-square','','inherit','open','closed','','zoom-whitening-square','','','2016-03-29 21:26:46','2016-03-29 21:26:46','',4100,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/zoom-whitening-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4110,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:28:56','2016-03-29 21:28:56','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hZbbmvPP5jI\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/hZbbmvPP5jI/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <small><em>What are My Options for Fixing Crooked Teeth?</em></small>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <p>Porcelain veneers are one of the most common ways to transform your smile. If you’re curious about porcelain veneers then please keep reading. We’re going to shed some light on how Dr. Blevins uses CEREC® technology to craft porcelain veneers with minimal prep time, in just one day.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <h3>What are porcelain veneers?</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>Porcelain veneers (often referred to as dental veneers) are comprised of a thin piece of ceramic porcelain that is about the thickness of a contact lens. These thin, yet durable pieces of porcelain are perfectly crafted by <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins/\">Dr. Blevins</a> in our office to match the natural look, shape, and color of your teeth. Our veneers will give you a natural-looking, bright smile!</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JYV0V0nXZls\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/JYV0V0nXZls/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <small><em>What are Porcelain Dental Veneers?</em></small>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Odc_y_E9eWE\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/Odc_y_E9eWE/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>What Does Getting Veneers Entail?</em></small></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <h3>The Procedure</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>The first step toward achieving the smile of your dreams with porcelain veneers is scheduling your cosmetic dentistry consultation with Dr. Blevins. Many people have had porcelain veneers completed by Dr. Blevins in Mullins.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>On the day of your consultation, you’ll meet with Dr. Blevins to discuss how you want your smile to look. Do you feel your teeth are too big? Too small? Do you want your teeth to be whiter? Are you unsatisfied with the gap in between your front teeth? This are all problems that porcelain veneers from Blevins Dentistry can fix!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After you and Dr. Blevins both agree on your goals and expectations, we then use our CEREC® technology, which enables us to craft custom porcelain veneers to your exact specifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The best part? We can do this in just one day right here in our own office! No outside dental labs needed.</strong></p> \r\n\r\n<p>It’s important to note that veneers are a non-reversible procedure because we will need to remove some of your tooth enamel before placing the veneers. Typically, patients will get anywhere from 6-10 veneers in order to improve their smile and self-confidence, and get the results they are looking for.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b1hkXgPPl00\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/b1hkXgPPl00/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <h3>Are veneers right for me?</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>If you think porcelain veneers may be an option for you, then we encourage you to contact our Mullins, SC dental office and schedule your cosmetic dentistry consultation today. We look forward to seeing you and transforming your smile into something you can’t wait to show off to others!</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr /> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after9.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after9-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after9\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4328\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after10.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after10-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after10\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4329\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after13.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after13-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after13\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4332\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after12.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after12-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after12\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4331\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6 offset-lg-3\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after11.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after11-1024x444.jpg\" alt=\"before-after11\" width=\"625\" height=\"271\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4330\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Single Visit Veneers','','publish','closed','closed','','single-visit-veneers','','','2017-09-27 17:50:09','2017-09-27 17:50:09','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4110',0,'page','',0),(4112,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:29:35','2016-03-29 21:29:35','','veneers-square','','inherit','open','closed','','veneers-square-2','','','2016-03-29 21:29:35','2016-03-29 21:29:35','',4110,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4114,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:30:24','2016-03-29 21:30:24','','veneers-square1','','inherit','open','closed','','veneers-square1','','','2016-03-29 21:30:24','2016-03-29 21:30:24','',4110,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4119,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:34:09','2016-03-29 21:34:09','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3969\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"box1\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3969 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Bone grafts for the dental implant procedure</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>A bone graft procedure allows patients to still receive implants even though he or she may not have a sufficient amount of bone. The right amount of bone is needed in order for the implant to have a stable foundation within the jaw bone.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Bone grafts have also been shown to slow down the progression of bone loss in the jaw area.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Dr. Blevins will determine which type of bone graft is needed— alloplast, autogenous, xenograft, or allograft.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>After the procedure, your implant dentist will talk to you about the healing and recovery period, which may take up to three months for a full recovery. During this time, you will follow certain post-operative instructions, including restrictions and requirements.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Once the bone graft heals properly, dental implants can be placed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are interested in dental implants, call Blevins Dentistry in Mullins, SC today.</p> ','Bone Grafting','','publish','closed','closed','','bone-grafting','','','2017-04-06 21:29:17','2017-04-06 21:29:17','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4119',0,'page','',0),(4125,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:39:40','2016-03-29 21:39:40','<div class=\"row align-items-center text-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Du1krP6hBrA\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/Du1krP6hBrA/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>Am I A Candidate For Dental Implants?</em></small></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5brsnWhN_lQ\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/5brsnWhN_lQ/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>Options to Restore Teeth Lost Due to Decay</em></small></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Perhaps you’ve already talked to a dentist about dental implants, and you’re just deciding whether or not you want implants. Or maybe you are in the process of learning about implants and you’re wondering if they’ll solve your dental problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have missing teeth, you probably want a solution pretty quickly. And if you’re suffering with a loose-fitting denture or bridge, a solution can’t come your way fast enough.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Dental implants may be the best option for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>What are dental implants?</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>Dental implants take the place of missing teeth. The biocompatible titanium screw (the actual dental implant) becomes your new tooth’s root. It is securely placed in the jawbone for a long-lasting fit.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/implant-square2.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/implant-square2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3983 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Dental implants can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>provide extra support for a loose-fitting bridge or denture.</li>\r\n	<li>replace one or more missing teeth.</li>\r\n	<li>restore the functionality of your teeth so you can speak, eat, and chew without problems.</li>\r\n	<li>enhance facial structure.</li>\r\n	<li>help prevent bone loss in the jaw area.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iMygYrAcyPw\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/iMygYrAcyPw/hqdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p class=\"text-center\"><em>Are Dental Implants Painful?</em></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NLXQfocrzdU\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/NLXQfocrzdU/hqdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p class=\"text-center\"><em>How Long Will Dental Implants Last?</em></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-sm-6\">\r\n    https://www.instagram.com/p/BFEoDIwnknp/?taken-by=blevinsdentistry\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-sm-6\">\r\n    https://www.instagram.com/p/BHk5DLeBiYj/?taken-by=blevinsdentistry\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>The dental implant procedure</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>The implant procedure can be well worth the time and effort. This is especially true for those who may need a bone graft or other restorative procedures.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>For implant cases, the process of osseointegration needs to occur so the bone can fuse properly with the titanium screw. This ensures a long-lasting, solid foundation for the new tooth.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>After the bone fuses successfully, a customized abutment will be placed on top of the implant. Finally, a customized dental crown will be placed on top of the abutment.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Your new tooth will look natural and will function just like your natural teeth.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-implant-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4129\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-implant-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"dental implant procedure\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4129 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Benefits of dental implants</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Patients can brush and floss their teeth like normal. You don’t need any special care instructions for the new implants.</li>\r\n	<li>Dental implants help to prevent bone loss in the jaw area, as well as preventing gum recession, since the implants fuse with the jawbone.</li>\r\n	<li>With dental implants, patients can speak, eat, and chew normally again.</li>\r\n	<li>Unlike the dental bridge procedure, dental implants do not need the surrounding teeth for support. So this means, with dental implants, the surrounding teeth do not become altered in any way during the implant process.</li>\r\n	<li>Dental implants will look and feel like your natural teeth (not fake or unnatural)!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I expect after treatment?</h3>\r\n<p>While dental implants can restore your smile and self confidence, it is important that you take care of your implants after your procedure, just like you would your natural teeth! You\'ll want to brush twice a day, and floss daily.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>You can schedule all future dental appointments with Blevins Dentistry (including oral exams, cleanings, and implant checkups) to ensure that your implants, teeth, and gums remain healthy!</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Dental implants at Blevins Dentistry</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are interested in learning more about dental implants or if you want to see if they are right for you, call <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com\">Blevins Dentistry</a> today for an appointment.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>We will gladly listen to your concerns and determine if dental implants are right for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We serve the following areas and cities: Mullins, Loris, Aynor, Dillon, Latta, Marion, Conway, North Myrtle & Myrtle Beach, Longs, Little River, and Florence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We look forward to serving you!</p>','Dental Implants','','publish','closed','closed','','dental-implants','','','2017-09-27 17:48:19','2017-09-27 17:48:19','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4125',0,'page','',0),(4127,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:40:16','2016-03-29 21:40:16','','implant-square2','','inherit','open','closed','','implant-square2-2','','','2016-03-29 21:40:16','2016-03-29 21:40:16','',4125,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/implant-square2-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4129,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:40:57','2016-03-29 21:40:57','','dental-implant-square','','inherit','open','closed','','dental-implant-square','','','2016-03-29 21:40:57','2016-03-29 21:40:57','',4125,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-implant-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4131,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:44:06','2016-03-29 21:44:06','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/extractions-sqaure.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4133\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/extractions-sqaure-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"extractions-sqaure\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4133 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Gentle tooth extractions are sometimes necessary</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>There are times when a tooth extraction is the only option. A few examples of when an extraction may be needed:</p> \r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If wisdom teeth need to be removed.</strong> These are the four molars in the far back of the mouth.</li> \r\n	<li><strong>A dental abcess, which is a pocket of infection near a tooth.</strong> An extraction may be needed if a root canal or another treatment method isn’t an option.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Getting dentures or dental implants.</strong> These procedures may require one or more teeth to be extracted.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>A severely decayed tooth.</strong> If a crown or a filling will not be sufficient to restore the tooth, an extraction may be the only option.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <p>Patients may need a tooth extracted in order to have a healthy mouth.</p>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>  \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Don’t worry, though, because we offer nitrous oxide and oral sedation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You don’t have to feel nervous or anxious about getting an extraction. We offer nitrous oxide and oral sedation so that patients can feel relaxed and at ease for their appointment.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>If you would like to learn more about sedation, or to find out if it’s right for you, call our office to schedule an appointment.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Extractions are sometimes necessary. You can find comfort in knowing that Dr. Blevins is skilled at gentle tooth extractions.</p>','Extractions','','publish','closed','closed','','extractions','','','2017-04-06 21:36:15','2017-04-06 21:36:15','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4131',0,'page','',0),(4133,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:46:55','2016-03-29 21:46:55','','extractions-sqaure','','inherit','open','closed','','extractions-sqaure','','','2016-03-29 21:46:55','2016-03-29 21:46:55','',4131,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/extractions-sqaure.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4136,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:50:03','2016-03-29 21:50:03','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3969\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"box1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3969 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Fixing a gummy smile with gum lifts or gum contouring</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>When patients have an overgrowth of gum tissue, the gums cover the teeth more than usual. This leads some patients to feel self conscious about their smile. However, it can be fixed with a gum lift or a gum contouring procedure.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>The gum lift follows three steps:</p>\r\n\r\n    <ol> \r\n	<li>Gentle sedation is given to the patient to ensure maximum comfort.</li>\r\n	<li>The dentist will gently raise the gums or remove part of the gum tissue typically by using a laser.</li> \r\n	<li>The dentist will contour or reposition the gum line to result in a beautiful smile. This phase is known by several names (gum contouring, gum recontouring, gum reduction, gum contouring surgery, or gum reshaping), and it can be done on its own without the gum lift phase.</li> \r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <p>The gum lift and contouring procedures do not require a lot of healing or recovery time. This is due to the fact that gum tissue heals very quickly.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<h3>You’ll love your new smile!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After the contouring or lift procedure, your teeth will appear longer and more proportional to each other. This will create an even-looking smile. Your confidence will soar because of your radiant, beautiful smile!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are interested in a gum lift or gum contouring, call Blevins Dentistry today.</p> ','Gum Lift / Contouring','','publish','closed','closed','','gum-lift-contouring','','','2017-04-06 21:39:17','2017-04-06 21:39:17','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4136',0,'page','',0),(4141,1001007,'2016-03-29 21:57:42','2016-03-29 21:57:42','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/laser-therapy-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4144\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/laser-therapy-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"laser-therapy-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4144 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Laser therapy can be used in several types of dental procedures, including:</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n      <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n	  <li>Crown Lengthening</li>\r\n	  <li>Oral Surgery</li>\r\n	  <li>Scaling and root planing (also called laser curettage)</li>\r\n	  <li>Periodontal Disease Treatment</li> \r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n        <ul>\r\n	  <li>Gum disease treatment</li>\r\n	  <li>Gum reshaping (also called gum contouring and gum reduction)</li>\r\n	  <li>Gingival plastic surgery (also called laser gum surgery)</li>\r\n	  <li>Frenectomies</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p>Rest assured, Dr. Todd Blevins is skilled at using laser therapy to solve these common dental problems.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Benefits of laser therapy in dentistry</h3>\r\nPatients can have a much more pleasant experience at their appointment because of laser therapy. More specifically:\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Laser therapy allows patients to have a nearly pain-free experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Lasers are safe and effective.</li> \r\n	<li>By opting for laser therapy, patients are decreasing the time it takes to recover and heal from certain procedures.</li> \r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Lasers reduce the amount of bleeding that may occur during or after procedures.</li> \r\n	<li>Lasers lower the infection rates since the laser beam seals off blood vessels and sterilizes the area.</li>\r\n	<li>Patients will experience less swelling, less pain, and less discomfort.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nSo if you’re ready to experience first class dentistry and you are interested in laser therapy, give us a call today. We look forward to meeting you. ','Laser Therapy','','publish','closed','closed','','laser-therapy','','','2017-04-06 21:33:57','2017-04-06 21:33:57','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4141',0,'page','',0),(4144,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:00:58','2016-03-29 22:00:58','','laser-therapy-square','','inherit','open','closed','','laser-therapy-square','','','2016-03-29 22:00:58','2016-03-29 22:00:58','',4141,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/laser-therapy-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4147,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:08:02','2016-03-29 22:08:02','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4098\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"smiling-woman-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4098 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Getting nitrous oxide for your dental appointments</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>Laughing gas can be used for minor procedures (i.e. cleanings/hygiene visits). It is a mild anesthetic comprised of 50% nitrous oxide and 50% oxygen.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>With nitrous oxide, you can experience several benefits:</p>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Minimized anxiety during your dental appointment.</li> \r\n	<li>Less pain/discomfort during the appointment.</li>\r\n	<li>Quick recovery time since it acts quickly and wears off quickly, too.</li>\r\n	<li>No driving restrictions after your appointment (you can even go back to work after your appointment).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are overly anxious or have dental phobias, nitrous oxide may be used in combination with oral conscious sedation. This combination helps patients feel completely relaxed and at ease during the appointment. The combination produces a more deepened level of relaxation, while still being awake and fully conscious.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Is nitrous oxide right for you?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Most patients are candidates for nitrous oxide. The depth of relaxation can actually be adjusted depending on your level of anxiety.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr /> \r\n\r\n<h3>How does a patient receive nitrous oxide?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>While sitting in the dental chair, nitrous oxide is delivered through a simple nosepiece that is connected to oxygen and nitrous lines. Patients take normal breaths through the nose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While patients don’t laugh (as the nickname implies), he or she will feel a pleasant euphoria with feelings of warmth, security, and a slight numbness.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Nitrous oxide may be the best solution to \"take the edge off\" for your next appointment. If you are interested in learning more or if you’d like to see if nitrous oxide can be given at your next appointment, call Blevins Dentistry today.</p>','Nitrous Oxide','','publish','closed','closed','','nitrous-oxide','','','2017-04-06 21:06:12','2017-04-06 21:06:12','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4147',0,'page','',0),(4152,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:12:04','2016-03-29 22:12:04','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-7\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=37Wirk6hrGc\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/37Wirk6hrGc/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-5\">\r\n    <h3>Oral appliance therapy for snoring and OSA</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p class=\"lead\">At Blevins Dentistry, we offer oral appliance therapy (OAT) to help OSA patients and those who snore constantly.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Blevins offers an effective solution— a safe, effective sleep appliance for those who suffer from snoring and mild to moderate OSA. Many patients love this mouth guard!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The appliance is similar to a sports mouth guard. It is comfortable to wear and not too bulky.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>For many OSA sufferers, the continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP) machine is a common treatment option. However, it is not the best option for some patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oral appliance therapy is a great alternative to CPAP therapy. The mouth appliance will hold the lower jaw slightly forward and keep the airway open while sleeping. This helps to prevent snoring, but also enables easier breathing without disruptions.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Choose oral appliance therapy at Blevins Dentistry</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>Obstructive sleep apnea is a serious medical condition that requires effective, timely treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>If you are interested in finding out whether or not oral appliance therapy is right for you, call Blevins Dentistry in Mullins, SC today.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>We look forward to providing you with a solution for your OSA and snoring problems.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sleep-apnea-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4155\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sleep-apnea-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"sleep-apnea-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4155 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> ','Oral Appliance Therapy','','publish','closed','closed','','oral-appliance-therapy','','','2017-09-27 17:47:49','2017-09-27 17:47:49','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4152',0,'page','',0),(4155,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:14:05','2016-03-29 22:14:05','','sleep-apnea-square','','inherit','open','closed','','sleep-apnea-square','','','2016-03-29 22:14:05','2016-03-29 22:14:05','',4152,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sleep-apnea-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4157,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:20:26','2016-03-29 22:20:26','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cancer-screening-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4160\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cancer-screening-square.jpg\" alt=\"cancer-screening-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-4160 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>What’s even more scary is this statistic: According to the National Cancer Institute, \"Each year in the United States, more than 21,000 men and 9,000 women are diagnosed with oral cancer (source: <a href=\"http://www.cancer.gov/publications/patient-education/wyntk-oral.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.cancer.gov/publications/patient-education/wyntk-oral.pdf</a>).\"</p>\r\n\r\n   <h3>Why not get screened for oral (mouth) cancer when possible?</h3> \r\n\r\n   <p>At Blevins Dentistry, we routinely evaluate our patients for oral cancer signs and symptoms during checkup appointments. This is just one more reason why it’s so important to go to your six-month checkup appointments.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Signs and symptoms that may indicate oral cancer</h3>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Difficulty swallowing</li>\r\n	<li>Red and/or white patches/spots anywhere in the mouth</li>\r\n	<li>Mouth sores that bleed easily or that do not heal</li>\r\n	<li>Tenderness, pain, or numbness anywhere on the lips or in the mouth</li>\r\n	<li>A lump or a thickening, rough spot</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Pain while speaking, chewing, swallowing, and/or moving the jaw or tongue</li>\r\n	<li>Loose teeth</li>\r\n	<li>Changes in how your dentures fit</li>\r\n	<li>Changes in your bite</li>\r\n	<li>Persistent sore throat</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>If you see signs of oral cancer, schedule an appointment with the doctor as soon as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr /> \r\n\r\n<h3>Comprehensive oral cancer screenings at the dentist office</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We want you to have a healthy mouth for many years to come. If you’re concerned about oral cancer, speak with Dr. Blevins, especially if you are at risk.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>The following are risk factors for oral cancer:</p> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Smoking cigars, pipes, cigarettes, or other tobacco products</li>\r\n	<li>Using smokeless tobacco</li>\r\n	<li>Excessive sun exposure</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Family history of cancer</li>\r\n	<li>Excessive alcohol consumption</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to the HPV-16 virus</li>\r\n	<li>Being a male over age 50</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>	 \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you don’t identify with any of these risk factors, you can still get oral cancer. Just remember that early diagnosis and treatment is very important for cancer survival.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr /> \r\n\r\n<h3>How do we check for oral cancer?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We will complete a visual exam of your mouth (teeth, lips, and gums) and throat to look for signs of cancer. We will look for any abnormalities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If we see anything abnormal, we may collect cells from the area of concern by using a simple brush test. The sample will get sent to the laboratory for analysis, and we’ll discuss the results with you when finished.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are concerned about oral cancer and you’d like to get screened today, call Blevins Dentistry for an appointment.</p> ','Oral Cancer Screening','','publish','closed','closed','','oral-cancer-screening','','','2017-04-06 19:59:56','2017-04-06 19:59:56','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4157',0,'page','',0),(4160,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:21:50','2016-03-29 22:21:50','','cancer-screening-square','','inherit','open','closed','','cancer-screening-square','','','2016-03-29 22:21:50','2016-03-29 22:21:50','',4157,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cancer-screening-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4165,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:27:17','2016-03-29 22:27:17','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sedation-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4168\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sedation-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"oral sedation dentistry\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4168 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Well you don’t have to feel that way any longer when you choose <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com\">Blevins Dentistry</a>. We offer oral sedation (also referred to as oral conscious sedation).</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>You don’t have to feel anxious or uncomfortable any longer.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Oral sedation at the dentist’s office</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>Oral sedation is typically administered in pill format. It is taken prior to the procedure so patients can feel less anxious and less apprehensive.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Throughout the procedure, you will be fully conscious, but still relaxed and at ease. That means you’ll still be able to answer the doctor’s questions and communicate.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Is oral sedation right for you?</h3>\r\n<p>If you can relate to any of these statements, oral sedation may be right for you:</p>\r\n \r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>I suffer from extreme anxiety or fear during or prior to dental appointments.</li>\r\n	<li>I have a hard time getting numb and/or staying numb at dental appointments.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>I have a severe gag reflex that makes it more difficult for the dentist to complete procedures.</li>\r\n	<li>I am getting multiple procedures done in one appointment.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, oral sedation can be used for many different dental procedures, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/root-canal-therapy/\">Root canals</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/extractions/\">Extractions</a></li>\r\n	<li>Soft tissue grafts</li>\r\n	<li>Crown lengthening</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/gum-lift-contouring/\">Gum lifts</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/\">Dental implants</a></li>\r\n	<li>Hard tissue grafts</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/bone-grafting/\">Bone grafts</a></li>\r\n	<li>Biopsies</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Choose oral sedation for your next dentist appointment</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Oral sedation is a safe way to feel relaxed and at ease at your next dental appointment. Just remember that you must have someone transport you back home after the appointment since you won’t be able to drive.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>If you’re interested in learning more or if you’d like to find out if oral sedation is right for you, call Blevins Dentistry today for an appointment.</p> ','Oral Sedation','','publish','closed','closed','','oral-sedation','','','2017-04-06 21:03:01','2017-04-06 21:03:01','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4165',0,'page','',0),(4168,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:28:22','2016-03-29 22:28:22','','sedation-square','','inherit','open','closed','','sedation-square','','','2016-03-29 22:28:22','2016-03-29 22:28:22','',4165,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sedation-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4171,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:32:37','2016-03-29 22:32:37','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cleanings-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4054\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cleanings-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"cleanings-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4054 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>We love teaching our patients about oral wellness for a long-lasting, healthy smile. Our dental office and the American Dental Association (ADA), recommend the following for optimal oral wellness:</p>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Brushing 2-3 times per day</li>\r\n	<li>Flossing 1-2 times per day</li>\r\n	<li>Getting routine checkups and professional cleanings from your dentist once every 6 months</li>\r\n	<li>Limiting your intake of foods and beverages that contain high sugar</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\n    <p>And if you have kids, don’t forget to teach them healthy oral habits, too.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Regular 6-month checkup appointments are important</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Regular checkup appointments allow us to keep an eye on potential problems in your mouth and to provide treatment when necessary.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Catching many types of dental problems early on can decrease the chances of more threatening issues down the road (i.e. periodontal disease).</p> \r\n\r\n<p>For instance, untreated gum disease, which can lead to periodontal disease) has been linked to serious health problems, such as: birth complications, stroke, diabetes, heart problems, and other serious illnesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Preventive dentistry for healthy teeth and gums</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>We offer several preventive dentistry services, including:</p> \r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Teeth cleanings (including fluoride treatments)</li>\r\n	<li>Teeth polishing</li>\r\n	<li>Dental sealants</li>\r\n	<li>Digital x-rays</li>\r\n	<li>Oral cancer screenings</li>\r\n	<li>Oral hygiene instructions</li>\r\n	<li>Comprehensive oral examinations</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4098\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"smiling-woman-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4098 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>An emphasis on oral wellness</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Blevins Dentistry offers customized oral wellness programs for each patient. We treat you as part of our family here; not just another number like some dental offices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here at our office you can look forward to unique, customized dental screenings at your appointments. They are designed to meet your specific dental goals and needs.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Our services promote healthy teeth and gums so you can smile with confidence. Schedule your consultation appointment today!</p>','Oral Wellness','','publish','closed','closed','','oral-wellness','','','2017-04-06 20:46:03','2017-04-06 20:46:03','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4171',0,'page','',0),(4179,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:44:11','2016-03-29 22:44:11','<h1 class=\"text-center\">PRF for Faster Healing</h1>\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p class=\"lead text-center\">Platelet rich fibrin (PRF) is a by-product of plasma (blood) with high levels of platelets. PRF is actually produced from patient’s blood so disease transmission is not an issue. In dentistry, PRF is very safe to use and offers many benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/blevins-team-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4182\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/blevins-team-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"blevins-team-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4182 img-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nPlatelet rich fibrin is used when patients need certain restorative dentistry services, such as: \r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>sinus lifts</li>\r\n	<li>ridge modifications</li>\r\n	<li>bone grafting</li>\r\n	<li>cleft lip and palate procedures</li>\r\n	<li>dental implants</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n\r\nAs an example, when PRF is added to a dental implant site in the mouth, the bone will grow more quickly. Platelet rich fibrin speeds up dental implant placement and healing for many patients. \r\n\r\nWhen used in dentistry, PRF allows patients to take advantage of faster healing times for restorative dental procedures.\r\n\r\n<hr /> \r\n\r\n<h3>Restorative dentistry at Blevins Dentistry</h3>\r\nDr. Todd Blevins of Blevins Dentistry in Mullins, South Carolina enjoys restoring patient’s smiles using the latest techniques and innovative technology. \r\n\r\nIf you would like to schedule an appointment today to find out if restorative dentistry is right for you, call our office today or contact us through our website.\r\n\r\nBlevins Dentistry — Five Star Service. First Class Smiles. \r\n\r\nWe look forward to meeting you. ','PRF for Faster Healing','','publish','closed','closed','','prf-for-faster-healing','','','2016-04-04 18:18:50','2016-04-04 18:18:50','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4179',0,'page','',0),(4184,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:49:09','2016-03-29 22:49:09','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-3\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/toothache-tooth-pain-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4186\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/toothache-tooth-pain-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"toothache-tooth-pain-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4186 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-9\">\r\n    <p>If a large cavity goes untreated, the harmful bacteria can damage the pulp, and this oftentimes results in a toothache.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>So then what happens? How does this get fixed?</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Well, if the inflammation and infection go untreated, it can lead to a painful abscess. So be sure to get evaluated and treated as soon as possible.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr /> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-10 offset-lg-1\">\r\n    <h3>Recommended treatment</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>When the pulp of permanent or primary teeth get damaged or infected, root canal treatment or endodontic treatment is recommended. These procedures can potentially save the natural teeth.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>The process of removing the infected, damaged pulp and placing the medicated filling is the actual \"pulpotomy.\" Today, the term \"pulpotomy\" is oftentimes used to describe the entire process, which also includes the placement of medication in the pulp space.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>When a pulpotomy is performed on baby teeth, it is sometimes referred to as a “baby tooth root canal,” even though it’s technically not a root canal treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Dentists who perform a pulpotomy try to keep the canal pulp healthy and alive, which in turn, saves the natural tooth. Patients will receive a local anesthetic for this procedure to remain comfortable and pain free.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> ','Pulpotomy','','publish','closed','closed','','pulpotomy','','','2017-04-06 20:36:12','2017-04-06 20:36:12','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4184',0,'page','',0),(4186,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:50:03','2016-03-29 22:50:03','','toothache-tooth-pain-square','','inherit','open','closed','','toothache-tooth-pain-square','','','2016-03-29 22:50:03','2016-03-29 22:50:03','',4184,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/toothache-tooth-pain-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4190,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:52:39','2016-03-29 22:52:39','<p>Root canal therapy is also referred to as endodontic therapy. We use the best anesthetics to ensure the patient is comfortable throughout the procedure.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>But what exactly is root canal treatment? Why do patients need \"a root canal?\"</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Facts about root canal treatment</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p>Root canal therapy is the process of removing decayed or infected tooth matter (inside of the tooth), along with the tooth’s nerve.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>There are three goals for root canal therapy:</p> \r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>to restore the natural tooth’s strength</li>\r\n	<li>to prevent future infections</li>\r\n	<li>to remove all decay and/or infection</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/root-canal-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4192\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/root-canal-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"root-canal-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4192 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Root canal therapy at Blevins Dentistry</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you experience tooth sensitivity, toothaches, or swelling, get evaluated by your dentist today. Prompt treatment in the form of root canal therapy can help save your natural tooth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Without prompt treatment, the infection can spread, which can cause a painful abscess, bone loss, or other serious health/dental problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you would like to schedule your appointment today, call <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com\" target=\"_blank\">Blevins Dentistry</a>.</p>','Root Canal Therapy','','publish','closed','closed','','root-canal-therapy','','','2017-04-06 20:38:49','2017-04-06 20:38:49','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4190',0,'page','',0),(4192,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:53:27','2016-03-29 22:53:27','','root-canal-square','','inherit','open','closed','','root-canal-square','','','2016-03-29 22:53:27','2016-03-29 22:53:27','',4190,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/root-canal-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4194,1001007,'2016-03-29 22:56:54','2016-03-29 22:56:54','<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g-jjJ1ykFV8\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/g-jjJ1ykFV8/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PNU-U6MzUwQ\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/PNU-U6MzUwQ/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://birdeye.com/embed/v4/150419314862312/3/3196112957\"></script><div id=\"bf-revz-widget-3196112957\" style=\"-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch;\"><div class=\"bf-dv\"><span class=\"bf-spn\">provided by <a class=\"bf-pro\" href=\"http://www.killershark.me/\" target=\"_blank\">Killer Shark Marketing</a></span></div></div>\r\n<hr>\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-3\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-patient-special-exam-xrays.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-patient-special-exam-xrays-192x300.jpg\" alt=\"new-patient-special-exam-xrays\" width=\"192\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4372\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-9\">\r\n    <p>Dr. Blevins says, \"The patients that we treat in our office are amazing. Developing lasting relationships with individuals and families was one of the main reasons I chose general dentistry as a profession. I want to thank each one for their feedback and reviews that will be shared with potential patients online. I know that this will help them decide to become part of our dental family as well as help our office to continually improve our patients\' experiences.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>We believe that communication is key to any relationship, so please feel free to call, email,  or contact us through our Facebook page if there is ever a concern about any aspect of your treatment.\"</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!--<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://emerit.medicaljustice.com/widgets/ratings-list-details1.aspx?member=blevinstodsc865\"></script>-->','Testimonials','','publish','closed','closed','','testimonials','','','2018-02-05 15:29:37','2018-02-05 15:29:37','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4194',0,'page','',0),(4200,1001007,'2016-03-29 23:06:00','2016-03-29 23:06:00','','Contact','','publish','closed','closed','','contact','','','2017-04-07 14:12:38','2017-04-07 14:12:38','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4200',0,'page','',0),(4209,1001007,'2016-03-31 04:15:19','2016-03-31 04:15:19','','slide2-new','','inherit','open','closed','','slide2-new','','','2016-03-31 04:16:14','2016-03-31 04:16:14','',3988,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/slide2-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4227,1001007,'2016-03-31 18:36:14','2016-03-31 18:36:14','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4062\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"periodontal disease treatment\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4062 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>It’s true. That’s why, at <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com\" target=\"_blank\">Blevins Dentistry</a>, we offer several periodontics service to help maintain your healthy teeth and gums for many years to come.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>Our hygienists and dentist are trained to offer effective periodontal disease and gum disease treatments with both surgical and non-surgical treatment options.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Catching gum disease early on</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It is very important to catch gum disease early, before it progresses to periodontal disease. Unfortunately most patients ignore these early warning signs of gum disease:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gums that become soft to the touch over time.</li>\r\n	<li>Gums that look irritated instead of the healthy pink color they should be.</li>\r\n	<li>Minor bleeding when brushing your teeth.</li>\r\n	<li>Gums that become discolored, like a dark red color instead of a healthy pink color.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you notice any of these symptoms, don’t ignore them. Schedule your appointment as soon as possible to get treated for gum disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Signs of periodontal disease</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Untreated gum disease can progress to a more serious problem—periodontal disease. Signs and symptoms include:</p> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Inflamed, swollen gums</li>\r\n	<li>Loose teeth</li>\r\n	<li>Receding gums</li>\r\n	<li>Bright red or purple gums</li>\r\n	<li>Tender, sensitive gums</li>\r\n	<li>Mouth sores</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Persistent bad breath (halitosis)</li>\r\n	<li>Persistent bad taste in the mouth</li>\r\n	<li>Spaces in between the teeth that develop over time</li>\r\n	<li>Changes in the way the teeth fit together when biting down</li>\r\n	<li>Pus between your gum line and teeth (pyorrhea)</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>If you notice any of these symptoms, call your dentist as soon as possible for an evaluation.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>The risks of untreated periodontal disease</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Without timely, effective treatments, periodontal disease can lead to:</p> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>heart attack</li>\r\n	<li>pancreatic cancer</li>\r\n	<li>diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>stroke</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lf-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>premature birth</li>\r\n	<li>respiratory disease</li>\r\n	<li>digestive disorders</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Don’t put yourself at risk any longer. If you suspect <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/gum-disease-care/\" target=\"_blank\">periodontal disease or gum disease</a>, call your dentist for an appointment today. At Blevins Dentistry, we will carefully evaluate your symptoms, teeth, and gums during your periodontal checkup appointment, and provide periodontics treatment when necessary.</p> \r\n\r\n ','Periodontics','','publish','closed','closed','','periodontics','','','2017-04-06 20:42:23','2017-04-06 20:42:23','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4227',0,'page','',0),(4232,1001007,'2016-03-31 20:01:35','2016-03-31 20:01:35','<h1 class=\"text-center\">New Patient Exam Special</h1>\r\n','New Patient Exam Special','','publish','closed','closed','','new-patient-exam-special','','','2018-01-12 19:28:26','2018-01-12 19:28:26','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4232',0,'page','',0),(4234,1001007,'2016-03-31 20:41:11','2016-03-31 20:41:11','','new-patient-special','','inherit','open','closed','','new-patient-special','','','2016-03-31 20:41:11','2016-03-31 20:41:11','',4232,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-patient-special.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4236,1001007,'2016-03-31 20:45:16','2016-03-31 20:45:16','First and foremost, we want to thank you for visiting our website. Here we provide information on a variety of dental procedures offered, as well as discuss the array of options you face when choosing a dentist. Whether you are in need of dental implants, porcelain veneers, teeth whitening, a routine cleaning, or any of the other services that we offer we look forward to seeing you soon. \r\n\r\nSimply fill out the contact form on this page, or give us a call in order to schedule your consultation today!','A Personal Welcome from Our Dental Office!','','publish','open','open','','a-personal-welcome-from-our-dental-office','','','2017-10-18 14:40:07','2017-10-18 14:40:07','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4236',0,'post','',0),(4268,1001007,'2016-04-05 22:52:11','2016-04-05 22:52:11','','crowns-square','','inherit','open','closed','','crowns-square-3','','','2016-04-05 22:52:11','2016-04-05 22:52:11','',4074,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crowns-square-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4269,1001007,'2016-04-05 22:56:57','2016-04-05 22:56:57','','blevins-building','','inherit','open','closed','','blevins-building','','','2016-04-05 22:56:57','2016-04-05 22:56:57','',5,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/blevins-building.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4270,1001007,'2016-04-05 23:06:37','2016-04-05 23:06:37','','Smile Gallery','','publish','closed','closed','','smile-gallery','','','2016-09-09 20:27:52','2016-09-09 20:27:52','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?post_type=gg_galleries&#038;p=4270',0,'gg_galleries','',0),(4273,1001007,'2016-04-22 16:34:12','2016-04-22 16:34:12','<p class=\"lead text-center\">Selecting a dentist is no easy decision. Sure you could choose the office closest to you, but is that the best decision for you and your family?</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nAt Blevins Dentistry, we believe that you deserve nothing but the best dental care, which is what we strive to give our patients each and every day. So whether you’re new to the Mullins area or you’re simply looking for a new dentist, we would love to meet you! \r\n\r\nIn fact, here are a few reasons we believe you should choose us as your new dental office:\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">1</span> Practicing dentistry in Mullins since 1998</h3>\r\n\r\nWhile experience isn’t everything, it’s very important in dentistry. <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins/\">Dr. Todd Blevins</a> has been practicing dentistry in Mullins since 1998, and in that time, has routinely seen patients from Florence, Myrtle Beach, Dillon, Latta, Loris, Conway, Aynor, and many surrounding areas. \r\n\r\nWhether you simply need a routine cleaning or you’re looking for a dentist who can per-form advanced cosmetic or restorative dental procedures, <strong>Dr. Blevins and his team have the experience and expertise to get the job done.</strong> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">2</span> A friendly, caring team of dental professionals</h3>\r\n<div><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"blevins-team-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"rounded-circle alignleft size-medium wp-image-4318\" /></div>\r\nWhile Dr. Blevins is one of the most accomplished dentists in South Carolina, he would be the first one to give the lion’s share of credit to the amazing team surrounding him. \r\n\r\nAfter all, when you visit a dental office your experience is largely shaped by the interactions you have with the people around you— the office staff, assistants, or dental hygienists. \r\n\r\n<strong>Choosing the right dentist for you is about more than just the qualifications or experience the dentist has; it’s about choosing an office with caring people and a warm, friendly atmosphere.</strong> \r\n\r\nIf you would like to learn a little more about our team members, <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/meet-our-staff/\">visit this page</a>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">3</span> An immaculate office with a classy, country club atmosphere</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-office-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-office-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"blevins-office-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4277 rounded-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nOur patients often tell us that our office has the \"look and feel\" of a classy, 5-star southern country club or a bed and breakfast. That is largely due to the excellent team at Blevins Dentistry who keep a neat and tidy office, helping patients feel right at home. \r\n\r\nWhether this is your first visit to our office or your 50th, <strong>you’ll feel right at home as our friendly team caters to you from the minute you walk through the door</strong>. Choosing a dental office is about much more than just choosing a dentist; it’s about selecting an office that will give you a comfortable, laid back, worry-free visit. \r\n\r\nIf cleanliness and friendliness are important to you when choosing a dental provider, you won’t find an office better suited for you than Blevins Dentistry. \r\n\r\nIn fact, as you’ll read about later in this article, we have patients who come to our office from 50 miles away because they love the unique, high-class, small town feel our dental practice has to offer. \r\n \r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">4</span> We stay at the forefront of dental technology</h3>\r\n\r\nWe don’t want to bore you too much with the geeky dental technology that we all love (after all, you probably don’t care about it quite as much as we do!), but it is important to us that our patients know <strong>our office is second to none in the area when it comes to technology.</strong> \r\n\r\nSpecifically, one of the technologies most beneficial to patients is our CEREC CAD/CAM machine, which helps us manufacture crowns, bridges, and veneers most of the time on the same day! \r\n\r\nIn the past, physical impressions needed to be taken, which then had to be sent off to a dental lab. With CEREC, however, a 3D image of your mouth is made and our machine uses that image to design and mill out crowns, bridges, or veneers for a precise fit every time. \r\n\r\nThe fact that patients can get <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/crowns-and-bridges/\">crowns in a day</a> or <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/single-visit-veneers/\">veneers in a day</a> is what gives Blevins Dentistry a unique advantage over other practices in the area. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">5</span> Continuing education for the entire team</h3>\r\n\r\nDr. Blevins and the entire team go above and beyond when it comes to continuing education. As we’ve already discussed, our entire team stays up to date with the latest dental techniques and developments in technology. We also take the time to educate ourselves so we can better serve our incredible patients. \r\n\r\nIn fact, Dr. Blevins has taken courses from some of the most highly regarded and esteemed organizations in dentistry including: The Dawson Academy, The Pankey Institute, CEREC Doctors, the Misch International Implant Institute™ and the Engel Institute for dental implant training. \r\n\r\nIf one of your chief concerns when selecting a new dentist is finding someone who has the skill set to properly care for your oral health, as well as help you accomplish your cosmetic or restorative dentistry goals, <strong>you won’t find many dentists more qualified than Dr. Blevins</strong>. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">6</span> Comprehensive dentistry focusing on total health and wellness</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"smiling-woman-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4098 rounded-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nA big part of what we do at Blevins Dentistry is educating our patients on the importance of oral health as it relates to overall health and wellness. \r\n\r\nA variety of studies have shown a potential link between gum disease and a variety of serious health issues (such as heart disease and diabetes), which is why we place so much emphasis on thorough, routine dental cleanings and exams. \r\n\r\nThe mouth really is the connection to the body. <strong>Keeping your mouth healthy is a first line of defense against not just gum disease or tooth decay, but overall health and wellness</strong>. \r\n\r\nTo learn more about our thorough dental exams and how they can help you keep a close eye on your overall health and wellness, <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/thorough-dental-exams/\">visit this page</a>. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">7</span> Conveniently located in the quaint town of Mullins</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Screen-Shot-2016-04-22-at-12.55.00-PM.png\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Screen-Shot-2016-04-22-at-12.55.00-PM-300x300.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2016-04-22 at 12.55.00 PM\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4278 rounded-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nMullins is a small, quaint town of about 5,000 residents and a far cry from the hustle and bustle of a big city. There is no traffic to fight and no difficulty finding a parking spot. You’ll always have a minute to catch your breath and inhale our fresh, country air. \r\n\r\nIf you live in Mullins you already know how great our small town is. However, if you’re from the surrounding area and maybe haven’t done more than just pass through, we encourage you to take an afternoon to visit our dental practice and do a little antique shopping while you’re at it! \r\n\r\nYou’ll find an abundance of small town charm and southern hospitality when visiting Mullins. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">8</span> Patients come see us from over 50 miles away</h3>\r\n\r\nWe may be located in the beautiful, quaint small town of Mullins, SC, but we aren’t just a small town dental practice with a few patients— far from it. In fact, <strong>Dr. Blevins is known as one of the most accomplished dentists in the entire state of South Carolina</strong>. In fact, patients routinely come to our office from up to and over 50 miles away.\r\n\r\nMaybe it’s the small town charm, the friendly atmosphere at our office, or the fact that patients love Dr. Blevins. Either way, if you are in or around one of the following areas (Mullins, Florence, Loris, Aynor, Dillon, Latta, Marion, Conway, North Myrtle & Myrtle Beach, Longs, and Little River), we encourage you to contact our practice and schedule your appointment with us. \r\n\r\nIt’s worth the drive…we promise!\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">9</span> Dentistry is in our DNA (4th generation dentist)</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/four-generations.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/four-generations-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"four-generations\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4279 rounded-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nDr. Todd Blevins certainly isn’t the first man in the family to be a dentist! In fact, Dr. Blevins often talks about how dentistry is in his blood, starting with his great grandfather, Dr. James Blevins. \r\n\r\nAfter James came Luke, Keith, and now your dentist, Dr. Todd Blevins. As you can see, Dr. Blevins didn’t become a dentist just because it’s considered a good profession. He did it because he has a passion for following in the footsteps of his father, grandfather, and great grandfather who all believed that patients come first, and are the most im-portant aspect of any successful dental office (followed closely by a great dental team, of course). \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">10</span> Currently accepting new patients</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-patients.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-patients-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"new-patients\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4280 rounded-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nWe believe in helping people in and around the Mullins area get the best dental care, and we believe we are the ones to provide it. This is why <strong>we routinely accept new patients and can usually schedule your appointment for the near future (no waiting months to see us)</strong>. \r\n\r\nWhether it’s a routine dental exam for you or your kids or you’re looking for more extensive dental work, such as a smile makeover or a full mouth reconstruction, we can take care of your needs and do so within a timeframe that makes sense for you. \r\n\r\nSo if you currently don’t have a dentist or you have to wait too long for an appointment, now is the perfect time to give our office a call to schedule your appointment/consultation. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">11</span> Dentistry is our ministry</h3>\r\n\r\nDr. Blevins knows that God uses him as a ministry tool each and every day when he shows up for work. At one point in college, Dr. Blevins actually thought of going into the field of full-time ministry, but in his heart he knew that God was going to make a dental office in Mullins, SC his mission field. \r\n\r\nDr. Blevins feels blessed to have the opportunity to visit places around the world where dental care is badly needed. As mentioned previously, Dr. Blevins is a 4th generation dentist, and he and his dad Keith routinely go on international mission trips to help those in need of dental care. \r\n\r\nWhether the mission field is on another continent or right here in Mullins, SC, Dr. Blevins is deeply committed to honoring God and serving others by providing his patients with excellent dental care. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">?</span> Is it time to visit the dentist? Are you ready to experience the Blevins Dentistry difference?</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"doctor-patient-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4037 rounded-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nBy now we hope we’ve made a great case as to why you should choose us as your dentist if you’re in Mullins, Myrtle Beach, Florence, or any of the surrounding towns in South Carolina. \r\n\r\nWhether you need a thorough dental exam and cleaning, you’re interested in cosmetic dentistry, or you need a full mouth reconstruction, <strong>Dr. Todd Blevins and the team at Blevins Dentistry will make sure you get exactly what you need in order to leave our office with a healthy smile</strong>. \r\n\r\nSo what are you waiting for? <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">Contact us today to schedule your appointment with Dr. Blevins</a>.','11 Reasons to Choose Blevins Dentistry in Mullins, SC','','publish','open','open','','11-reasons-to-choose-blevins-dentistry-in-mullins-sc','','','2017-05-18 18:51:07','2017-05-18 18:51:07','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4273',0,'post','',0),(4277,1001007,'2016-04-22 16:53:09','2016-04-22 16:53:09','','blevins-office-square','','inherit','open','closed','','blevins-office-square','','','2016-04-22 16:53:09','2016-04-22 16:53:09','',4273,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-office-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4278,1001007,'2016-04-22 16:55:45','2016-04-22 16:55:45','','Screen Shot 2016-04-22 at 12.55.00 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2016-04-22-at-12-55-00-pm','','','2016-04-22 16:55:45','2016-04-22 16:55:45','',4273,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Screen-Shot-2016-04-22-at-12.55.00-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4279,1001007,'2016-04-22 16:57:47','2016-04-22 16:57:47','','four-generations','','inherit','open','closed','','four-generations','','','2016-04-22 16:57:47','2016-04-22 16:57:47','',4273,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/four-generations.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4280,1001007,'2016-04-22 16:59:43','2016-04-22 16:59:43','','new-patients','','inherit','open','closed','','new-patients','','','2016-04-22 16:59:43','2016-04-22 16:59:43','',4273,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-patients.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4283,1001007,'2016-04-22 21:38:12','2016-04-22 21:38:12','[instagram-feed id=\"3136526937\"]','Social','','publish','closed','closed','','social','','','2017-04-07 14:45:08','2017-04-07 14:45:08','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4283',0,'page','',0),(4286,1001007,'2016-04-26 17:09:12','2016-04-26 17:09:12','','Screen Shot 2016-04-26 at 1.08.18 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2016-04-26-at-1-08-18-pm','','','2016-04-26 17:09:12','2016-04-26 17:09:12','',5,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Screen-Shot-2016-04-26-at-1.08.18-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4288,1001007,'2016-05-27 16:16:41','2016-05-27 16:16:41','','slide5-new','','inherit','open','closed','','slide5-new','','','2016-05-27 16:16:41','2016-05-27 16:16:41','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/slide5-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4289,1001007,'2016-05-27 16:20:44','2016-05-27 16:20:44','','slide4-new','','inherit','open','closed','','slide4-new-2','','','2016-05-27 16:20:44','2016-05-27 16:20:44','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/slide4-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4290,1001007,'2016-05-27 23:35:43','2016-05-27 23:35:43','<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"smiling-woman-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4098 img-circle\" />One question that consistently comes up during consultations with current patients or with those who are considering dental implants is, “Which is better— dental implants or dentures?” \r\n\r\nThe fact is this: if you’re missing one or more teeth and are looking for a solution, they can both be excellent options. \r\n\r\nIn this article, we’re going to discuss dental implants and dentures to determine which is right for you. As always, we invite you to <u><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">schedule your consultation</u></a>, where we can see you in person, discuss your needs and goals, and determine what is best for your unique situation. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>Let’s look at dentures first</h3>\r\n\r\nDo you remember when you were younger and one of your parents or grandparents had “false teeth” resting in a glass by the bathroom sink? Well, as you probably already know, those are dentures. \r\n\r\nDentures are a quick solution to fix your smile if you have no teeth and they can provide a decent level of support. That being said, they are actually far from the ideal solution. \r\n\r\nWhile traditional dentures are quickly becoming a thing of the past, one service that we offer at Blevins Dentistry that is increasing in popularity are <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/snap-in-dentures/\">implant-supported dentures</a> commonly referred to as an overdenture or snap-in dentures. \r\n\r\nSnap-in dentures typically require 2-4 dental implants on the bottom and 4-8 dental implants on the top. The denture then, literally, snaps into place quickly and easily. Since it is anchored to the jaw with sturdy dental implants, it can provide a great look, while supporting your facial structure. \r\n\r\nUnlike the dental implants that anchor snap-in dentures, the overdenture itself is removable, which can be either positive or negative depending on patient preference. One benefit of implant-supported dentures— they are much more stable than a cheap temporary denture that can rattle around in your mouth and make it difficult to eat certain foods. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>Dental implants: The gold standard </h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dentures-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"dentures-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4085 img-circle\" />For those patients who want to experience the very best in restorative dentistry, dental implants (when combined with crowns or a bridge) are an excellent option. \r\n\r\nDental implants take the place of your natural tooth root by using a titanium, biocompatible screw that is securely placed into the jaw bone. Many patients prefer dental implants due to their stability and because they last for a long time.\r\n\r\nHere are just a few of the many benefits of dental implants:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Implants can provide extra support for a loose-fitting bridge or denture.</li>\r\n<li>Implants can replace multiple missing teeth. </li>\r\n<li>Implants help you live a normal life (eat anything, speak better, etc.).</li>\r\n<li>Implants improve your facial structure.</li>\r\n<li>Implants prevent bone loss in the jaw area over time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nAnd much more. In fact, if you would like to see Dr. Blevins discuss dental implants on video and learn more about the dental implant procedure, please click here to <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/\">visit this page</a>. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>Which one is right for you?</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"doctor-patient-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4037 img-circle\" />Your goals, as well as a thorough examination of your dental history, are needed in order to tell you which procedure is best for you. We want to invite you to schedule your consultation with Dr. Blevins so you can meet him and go over any questions you may have. \r\n\r\nJust give our office a call or <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">contact us here</a> to schedule your consultation. We look forward to meeting you and figuring out together which treatment option is best to restore your smile and self-confidence. \r\n','Dental Implants vs. Dentures: Which is Best for You?','','publish','open','open','','dental-implants-vs-dentures-which-is-best-for-you','','','2016-11-03 17:42:52','2016-11-03 17:42:52','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4290',0,'post','',0),(4291,1001007,'2016-05-27 23:34:48','2016-05-27 23:34:48','','dentures-banner','','inherit','open','closed','','dentures-banner','','','2016-05-27 23:34:48','2016-05-27 23:34:48','',4290,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/dentures-banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4294,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:17','2016-06-17 14:21:17','','before-after1','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after1','','','2016-06-17 14:21:17','2016-06-17 14:21:17','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4295,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:18','2016-06-17 14:21:18','','before-after2','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after2','','','2016-06-17 14:21:18','2016-06-17 14:21:18','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4296,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:19','2016-06-17 14:21:19','','before-after3','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after3','','','2016-06-17 14:21:19','2016-06-17 14:21:19','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4297,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:22','2016-06-17 14:21:22','','before-after4','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after4','','','2016-06-17 14:21:22','2016-06-17 14:21:22','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4298,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:23','2016-06-17 14:21:23','','before-after5','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after5','','','2016-06-17 14:21:23','2016-06-17 14:21:23','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4299,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:24','2016-06-17 14:21:24','','before-after6','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after6','','','2016-06-17 14:21:24','2016-06-17 14:21:24','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after6.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4300,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:25','2016-06-17 14:21:25','','before-after7','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after7','','','2016-06-17 14:21:25','2016-06-17 14:21:25','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after7.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4301,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:21:28','2016-06-17 14:21:28','','before-after8','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after8','','','2016-06-17 14:21:28','2016-06-17 14:21:28','',4270,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-after8.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4302,1001007,'2016-06-17 14:26:39','2016-06-17 14:26:39','','slide3','','inherit','open','closed','','slide3-2','','','2016-06-17 14:26:39','2016-06-17 14:26:39','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/slide3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4304,1001007,'2016-07-01 19:20:56','2016-07-01 19:20:56','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-7 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JYV0V0nXZls\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/JYV0V0nXZls/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>What are Porcelain Dental Veneers?</em></small></p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-5\">\r\n    <p>Cosmetic dentistry is complicated, right? At least that’s what most people think. After all, you have to:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>Schedule your consultation</li>\r\n      <li>Meet with the doctor</li>\r\n      <li>Go home and evaluate your options</li>\r\n      <li>Maybe see multiple cosmetic dentists in the process</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>And then, even after all of that “legwork,” it still takes 2-4 visits to get the smile you want. Seems a little excessive, doesn’t it?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A lot of patients just get frustrated with the whole process and, as a result, end up doing nothing. Meanwhile, they wake up day after day, look in the mirror, and know that their smile isn’t what they want it to be.</p> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-5\">\r\n    <p>It doesn’t have to be that way. At Blevins Dentistry, we perform one of the most popular and effective cosmetic dentistry options (porcelain veneers) in just one visit with minimal prep time.</p> \r\n\r\n    <p>This means that you’ll never have to wait weeks for a dental lab to complete their work. And you won’t have to walk around with a set of temporary veneers while you’re waiting for your permanent veneers.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-7 text-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Odc_y_E9eWE\" class=\"lightbox\">\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/Odc_y_E9eWE/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <p><small><em>What Does Getting Veneers Entail?</em></small></p> \r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>How are we able to do it? </h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/cerec.jpg\" alt=\"cerec\" width=\"400\" height=\"251\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-4306\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We want to introduce you to a cutting-edge dental technology that our office has invested in over the last couple of years called <strong>CEREC®</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With our CEREC machine, we are able to take digital impressions of your teeth. After the impressions are taken, our milling machine then crafts perfect veneers that gives you the perfect shape and shade of veneer you are looking for.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>The end result is that our patients are able to get the veneers they’ve always wanted to fix their teeth without the hassle associated with traditional veneers. To give you an idea of what is possible with CEREC technology, here is a case study for you to view:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cereconline.com/two-veneers-with-cerec\">https://www.cereconline.com/two-veneers-with-cerec </a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>CEREC technology enables us to craft veneers that look natural and fit your mouth perfectly, right here in your Mullins, SC office.</p> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Are you a candidate for porcelain veneers?</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"veneers-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4112 img-circle\" />\r\n\r\n<p>It’s important to note that porcelain veneers are an irreversible cosmetic procedure, as some tooth enamel must be removed to ensure a secure fit and natural look. Porcelain veneers are typically best for patients who are looking to fix anywhere from 2-10 of their teeth and restore them to their natural beauty.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>If you have teeth that are severely stained, chipped, cracked, or misshapen, one-day porcelain veneers from Dr. Blevins may be the perfect solution for you. Please <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">contact our office today</a> in order to schedule your veneers consultation. <strong>Patients travel to our Mullins office from Florence, Loris, Aynor, Dillon, Latta, Marion, Conway, North Myrtle & Myrtle Beach, Longs, Little River and other surrounding areas for porcelain veneers.</strong></p> \r\n\r\n<p>You could be in and out of our office with a brand new smile in just a single day! Call us today to schedule your consultation. If you’re still on the fence, below you can read just a few of the reasons that many patients choose to visit our office for all of their cosmetic dentistry needs:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/11-reasons-to-choose-blevins-dentistry-in-mullins-sc/\">http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/11-reasons-to-choose-blevins-dentistry-in-mullins-sc/</a></p>','Veneers in a Day? It\'s Possible with CEREC Technology!','','publish','open','open','','veneers-in-a-day-its-possible-with-cerec-technology','','\nhttp://www.blevinsdentistry.com/11-reasons-to-choose-blevins-dentistry-in-mullins-sc/','2017-09-27 17:53:28','2017-09-27 17:53:28','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4304',0,'post','',0),(4305,1001007,'2016-07-01 19:18:23','2016-07-01 19:18:23','','veneers-banner','','inherit','open','closed','','veneers-banner','','','2016-07-01 19:18:23','2016-07-01 19:18:23','',4304,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/veneers-banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4306,1001007,'2016-07-01 19:20:04','2016-07-01 19:20:04','','cerec','','inherit','open','closed','','cerec','','','2016-07-01 19:20:04','2016-07-01 19:20:04','',4304,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/cerec.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4308,1001007,'2016-07-08 17:56:00','2016-07-08 17:56:00','<h3>What is L-PRF?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\"L-PRF™ is essentially a bioactive \'band-aid\' that is created from your own blood and then placed in your surgery sites to promote healing. A sample of your blood is collected in a tube, just as it would be for a blood test. Your doctor then uses the unique IntraSpin™ System to separate and concentrate certain important cells and active proteins by spinning your own blood in a dedicated centrifuge.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>After a fast preparation the bioactive clot, created just from your own blood, is now ideal for your procedure.  When placed in surgery sites, L-PRF releases your body’s own natural healing proteins, creating a more efficient network for cells to enhance the healing process.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Depending on your situation, your doctor may supplement your L-PRF clot with different biomaterials customized for your needs. For patients with significant bone loss, a combination of L-PRF and bone growth material may also be used to promote natural bone regeneration.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the Benefits of L-PRF?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>L-PRF promotes better healing from within by using your body\'s own natural, organic material to assist in the healing process (and avoiding chemicals). Here are just a few benefits:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>L-PRF uses an FDA-cleared medical device.</li>\r\n  <li>The procedure is a simple, natural, 100% holistic procedure.</li> \r\n  <li>No chemicals, foreign substances, or additives are used...just you!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Want to Learn More?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To learn more about L-PRF therapy, give our office a call today. We would love to speak with you in regards to your oral surgery options, your recovery, and how we can help you with our L-PRF therapy.</p>','L-PRF For Faster Healing','','publish','closed','closed','','l-prf-for-faster-healing','','','2017-04-06 21:30:45','2017-04-06 21:30:45','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4308',0,'page','',0),(4313,1001007,'2016-07-30 20:53:54','2016-07-30 20:53:54','<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crowns-square-2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"crowns-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4268 img-circle\" />When you look into the mirror, smile, and don’t like what you see, it can be very frustrating. After all, many people say that a smile is the window to the soul, and if you aren’t happy with your smile, it can have a substantial effect on your overall health and wellness. \r\n\r\nIf you are missing one or more teeth, we understand what you’re going through. It can lead to embarrassment and not wanting to smile in public. \r\n\r\nAt Blevins Dentistry, we don’t want you going through life feeling this way because we know there is a solution; a better way to restore your teeth and get the smile you’ve always wanted. \r\n\r\nIn this article, we’re going to discuss dental implants with crowns and how this combination of restorative and cosmetic procedures may be exactly what you are looking for. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>What are Dental Implants?</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/square-smile-2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"square-smile-2\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3966 img-circle\" />Dental implants use titanium screws to mimic your natural tooth roots. When implants are placed, they are inserted into your jawbone. After some time has passed, the implant will fuse together with your jawbone to create a strong foundation for your new tooth. \r\n\r\nOne common misconception many people have regarding dental implants is that any dentist can do them. In reality, many dental practices will actually refer you to a specialist who has additional experience placing implants. \r\n\r\nOf course, there is nothing wrong with this. However, many patients find it more convenient to have their implants placed by a dentist who can also perform routine dental exams, as well as cosmetic procedures. \r\n\r\nAt Blevins Dentistry, we take care of the entire dental implants procedure (as well as many other services) all under one roof. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>What About Abutments?</h3>\r\n\r\nWhile the abutment is definitely the “middle child” of the implants process, it plays the important role of connecting the titanium implant to the porcelain crown. \r\n\r\nTypically, a dental implant abutment can either be prefabricated or custom made. While the placement of the implant is the most important factor, custom abutments may be required in certain situations (Dr. Blevins will advise you on all aspects of the implant procedure, including which implant abutments should be used). \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>What are Porcelain Crowns?</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crowns-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"crowns-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4075 img-circle\" />Dental crowns are the only part of a dental implant that you will see once your procedure is complete. The titanium screws and abutments are “under the hood” so to speak. \r\n\r\nWhat’s unique about our dental practice is that we incorporate a leading technology known as CEREC into our dental crowns process. Using CEREC technology, we are able to manufacture your porcelain crowns in a single day…right in our office!\r\n\r\nIf you would like to learn more about the CEREC technology we use at Blevins Dentistry or to see a few videos where Dr. Blevins addresses some common concerns regarding dental implants, click the links below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/\">http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/crowns-and-bridges/\">http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/crowns-and-bridges/</a>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>So are Dental Implants with Crowns Right for You?</h3>\r\n\r\nIf you are missing one or more teeth, then dental implants combined with either porcelain crowns or a bridge may be the best treatment option to restore your smile and self confidence. \r\n\r\nPatients travel to our Mullins office from Florence, Loris, Aynor, Dillon, Latta, Marion, Conway, North Myrtle & Myrtle Beach, Longs, Little River and other surrounding areas for cosmetic, general, and restorative dental services. If you are in or around that area, please give our office a call to schedule your dental implants consultation today! \r\n','Dental Implants with Crowns: Restoring Your Smile & Self Confidence!','','publish','open','open','','dental-implants-with-crowns-restoring-your-smile-self-confidence','','','2016-11-03 17:41:55','2016-11-03 17:41:55','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4313',0,'post','',0),(4314,1001007,'2016-08-08 20:52:29','2016-08-08 20:52:29','','family-banner','','inherit','open','closed','','family-banner','','','2016-08-08 20:52:29','2016-08-08 20:52:29','',4313,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/family-banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4315,1001007,'2016-08-10 14:24:27','2016-08-10 14:24:27','','Slide1-new','','inherit','open','closed','','slide1-new-3','','','2016-08-10 14:24:27','2016-08-10 14:24:27','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Slide1-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4316,1001007,'2016-08-10 14:36:57','2016-08-10 14:36:57','','SlideBlev-New','','inherit','open','closed','','slideblev-new','','','2017-04-06 19:13:32','2017-04-06 19:13:32','',3988,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/SlideBlev-New.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4317,1001007,'2016-08-10 14:47:00','2016-08-10 14:47:00','','blevins-team-banner','','inherit','open','closed','','blevins-team-banner','','','2016-08-10 14:47:00','2016-08-10 14:47:00','',4273,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4318,1001007,'2016-08-10 14:47:56','2016-08-10 14:47:56','','blevins-team-square','','inherit','open','closed','','blevins-team-square-3','','','2016-08-10 14:47:56','2016-08-10 14:47:56','',4273,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4320,1001007,'2016-08-10 15:19:48','2016-08-10 15:19:48','','lisa-square','','inherit','open','closed','','lisa-square','','','2016-08-10 15:19:48','2016-08-10 15:19:48','',3999,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/lisa-square.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4323,1001007,'2016-08-31 15:21:09','2016-08-31 15:21:09','<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"box1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3969 img-circle\" />Whether you’ve been in a serious car wreck, had a trip and fall accident, or have suffered some type of sports-related injury, an accident is never something that you want to happen. Unfortunately, life happens and accidents are often a part of it. \r\n\r\nAfter serious facial trauma occurs, people oftentimes need extensive dental repair work done. While it may not be the first thing on your mind following an accident, eventually you will probably want to see what can be done to restore (or even improve upon) your natural smile. \r\n\r\nIf you’ve suffered dental trauma due to an accident and are looking at extensive dental work (often referred to as full mouth rehab or a full mouth reconstruction), Dr. Blevins can help. \r\n\r\nWhether you’ve had teeth knocked out or you’ve experienced damage to your jaw region, our goal is to use our skills and expertise to rebuild both the functionality and aesthetics of your teeth and jaws. \r\n\r\nIn this article, we’re specifically going to cover the variety of dental procedures that are often involved as part of the full mouth reconstruction process. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>What types of dental trauma often require treatment?</h3>\r\n\r\nWhile there are minor cases of dental trauma that may only require a small amount of dental bonding, more serious accidents that require full mouth reconstruction will likely exhibit some of the following problems:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>missing teeth</li>\r\n<li>injured and/or fractured/broken teeth</li>\r\n<li>severely worn-out or worn-down teeth</li>\r\n<li>severely decayed teeth</li>\r\n<li>severely eroded enamel</li>\r\n<li>soft tissue damage</li>\r\n<li>hard tissue (bones) damage</li>\r\n<li>skeletal injuries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYou’ll notice that some of these issues may be a direct result of your accident (such as broken teeth, missing teeth, or skeletal injuries), while others may be underlying problems that are oftentimes discovered only after an accident (like decaying teeth or eroded enamel). \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>What are the most common cosmetic & restorative procedures used in full mouth reconstruction cases?</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/implant-square2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"implant-square2\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3983 img-circle\" />At Blevins Dentistry, we only want to perform the procedures on patients that get results. We will never try to sell you on more services than you need in order to accomplish your goals. \r\n\r\nThat being said, these are a few of the more popular cosmetic & restorative procedures that we often use as part of the full mouth reconstruction process:\r\n\r\n<em>Dental implants:</em>\r\n\r\nImplants are titanium screws that integrate into your jawbone in order to anchor porcelain crowns, bridges, or even dentures. A dental implant acts as a natural tooth root for an artificial tooth. \r\n\r\nThe dental implant procedure is an invasive surgery and therefore many dentists do not perform this procedure. Dr. Blevins has placed implants for many, many patients, helping them achieve fantastic results. \r\n\r\n<em>Porcelain crowns and bridges:</em>\r\n\r\nPorcelain crowns and bridges are both cosmetic and restorative in nature. While the crown or bridge serves as the artificial teeth people will see, they also enable you to resume normal activities, such as chewing. \r\n\r\n<em>Veneers:</em>\r\n\r\nVeneers are about the thickness of a contact lens, covering the front of your teeth. It’s important to note that veneers are a non-reversible procedure, but if you’ve experienced severe breakage or chipping (especially with your front teeth), then veneers may be a perfect option for you. \r\n\r\nAlso, since Dr. Blevins stays at the forefront of dental technology and has invested heavily in CEREC technology, we can craft custom porcelain dental crowns and veneers in our office the same day of your appointment! \r\n\r\nFor more information on CEREC technology and how it is used to craft veneers and porcelain crowns, visit the links below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/crowns-and-bridges/\">CEREC porcelain crowns & bridges</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/single-visit-veneers/\">Single visit veneers with CEREC technology</a>\r\n\r\nThere are a wide variety of cosmetic and restorative procedures that may be used as part of a full mouth reconstruction procedure. For more information on full mouth rehab, click the link below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/full-mouth-rehab/\">http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/full-mouth-rehab/</a>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3>Need dental treatment after an accident? Contact Blevins Dentistry.</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/box2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"box2\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-3967 img-circle\" />If you’ve been injured in a car accident and live in or around the Mullins, Myrtle Beach, Florence, Aynor, or Loris area of South Carolina, we would love to meet you in person and discuss your needs. \r\n\r\nDr. Blevins is a highly decorated cosmetic and restorative dentist <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins/\">(read more about Dr. Blevins here)</a>, and patients frequently travel to our practice from around South Carolina for their cosmetic and restorative procedures. \r\n\r\nWhen you’re considering a significant amount of dental work, you want to make sure that you choose a dentist based on their experience and qualifications, not geography. It’s well worth driving a couple of hours or more to see one of the most qualified dentists in South Carolina! \r\n\r\nIf you need full mouth reconstruction after dental trauma, call our office today! ','What\'s Involved in a Full Mouth Reconstruction After an Accident or Trauma?','','publish','open','open','','whats-involved-in-a-full-mouth-reconstruction-after-an-accident-or-trauma','','','2016-11-03 17:41:29','2016-11-03 17:41:29','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4323',0,'post','',0),(4324,1001007,'2016-09-01 15:21:53','2016-09-01 15:21:53','','teeth-eating-banner','','inherit','open','closed','','teeth-eating-banner','','','2016-09-01 15:21:53','2016-09-01 15:21:53','',4323,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/teeth-eating-banner.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(4326,1001007,'2016-09-08 00:44:47','2016-09-08 00:44:47','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/lisa-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/lisa-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4320 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <p>Lisa has been Dr. Blevins’ Dental Assistant since June 2016. She received her certification from Florence Darlington Technical College. Lisa enjoys helping create and restore beautiful smiles, through the art of cosmetic dentistry.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Lisa has been in the dental field for over 16 years and especially loves assisting the doctor with crown and bridge work. Lisa resides in Marion with her husband, Todd, and their children Katie, Jenna and Evan.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Lisa J. Johnson','','publish','closed','closed','','lisa-j-johnson','','','2017-04-07 15:09:13','2017-04-07 15:09:13','',3999,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?page_id=4326',0,'page','',0),(4328,1001007,'2016-09-09 20:24:31','2016-09-09 20:24:31','','before-after9','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after9','','','2016-09-09 20:24:31','2016-09-09 20:24:31','',4095,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after9.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4329,1001007,'2016-09-09 20:24:32','2016-09-09 20:24:32','','before-after10','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after10','','','2016-09-09 20:24:32','2016-09-09 20:24:32','',4095,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after10.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4330,1001007,'2016-09-09 20:24:33','2016-09-09 20:24:33','','before-after11','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after11','','','2016-09-09 20:24:33','2016-09-09 20:24:33','',4095,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4331,1001007,'2016-09-09 20:24:35','2016-09-09 20:24:35','','before-after12','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after12','','','2016-09-09 20:24:35','2016-09-09 20:24:35','',4095,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after12.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4332,1001007,'2016-09-09 20:24:36','2016-09-09 20:24:36','','before-after13','','inherit','open','closed','','before-after13','','','2016-09-09 20:24:36','2016-09-09 20:24:36','',4095,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/before-after13.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4335,1001007,'2016-09-21 19:15:44','2016-09-21 19:15:44','','iwp_log_57e2dc60cd2bc','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_57e2dc60cd2bc','','','2016-09-21 19:15:44','2016-09-21 19:15:44','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_57e2dc60cd2bc/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4336,1001007,'2016-09-21 19:18:41','2016-09-21 19:18:41','','iwp_log_57e2dd11262e4','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_57e2dd11262e4','','','2016-09-21 19:18:41','2016-09-21 19:18:41','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_57e2dd11262e4/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4337,1001007,'2016-10-03 15:34:50','2016-10-03 15:34:50','','iwp_log_57f27a9a1d1bf','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_57f27a9a1d1bf','','','2016-10-03 15:34:50','2016-10-03 15:34:50','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_57f27a9a1d1bf/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4338,1001007,'2016-10-03 15:38:33','2016-10-03 15:38:33','','iwp_log_57f27b79696d2','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_57f27b79696d2','','','2016-10-03 15:38:33','2016-10-03 15:38:33','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_57f27b79696d2/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4339,1001007,'2016-10-03 15:42:45','2016-10-03 15:42:45','','iwp_log_57f27c75daf73','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_57f27c75daf73','','','2016-10-03 15:42:45','2016-10-03 15:42:45','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_57f27c75daf73/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4341,1001007,'2016-10-03 16:30:19','2016-10-03 16:30:19','<p class=\"lead\">Have you ever noticed someone’s smile get remarkably better overnight? Odds are, their new look is thanks to porcelain veneers (also known as dental veneers).</p>\r\n\r\nPorcelain veneers are thin shells of ceramic porcelain that are about the thickness of a contact lens. Despite being thin, they are built to last and are very strong. Each veneer is crafted to match the look and color of your teeth, providing a natural and bright smile. \r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins\">Dr. Blevins</a> has extensive experience providing porcelain veneers and giving people a smile of which they can be proud. Here are the top 5 benefits of getting porcelain veneers from Dr. Blevins:\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">1</span> Improve your smile</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/square-smile-2.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/square-smile-2-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"square-smile-2\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3966 img-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nIf you have chipped, discolored, or damaged teeth, smiling can sometimes feel embarrassing. We always start with a consultation where Dr. Blevins will ask how you want your smile to look. Do you think your teeth are too big or too small? Do you need to cover a chip? Do you want whiter teeth? \r\n\r\nWhatever your situation, we can help improve your smile. Dr. Blevins will craft veneers that are custom made to your needs and wants, ensuring you have a smile that gives you confidence.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">2</span> Done in One Day</h3>\r\nHistorically, dental veneers required a mold to be taken of your teeth. This mold was then sent to an off-site dental technician where veneers were created to fit the mold and then sent back to the dentist who originally took the mold. \r\n\r\nAt Blevins Dentistry, we have a better way. Using CEREC® technology, we are able to craft custom porcelain veneers to your exact specifications, and we can do it right here in the office. That means we can prepare and bond the veneers to your teeth on the same day! You’ll experience a lesser wait time and more time with your new smile.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">3</span> Our Dental Veneers Will Endure</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"veneers-square1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4114 img-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nIt’s important to know that porcelain veneers are permanent. In order to apply them, we need to remove some of the enamel from the teeth before placing the veneers. For this reason, we take extra care to ensure patients are happy with their design and color. \r\n\r\nIt’s a great advantage, however, to know that when you invest in your smile with veneers from Blevins Dentistry, your investment will not erode, break off, or need to be replaced any time soon (if ever).\r\n\r\nThanks to CEREC® technology, we can ensure your veneer fits perfectly with your actual tooth and creates a strong bond. We also use ceramic porcelain, which is a very strong material that won’t break easily.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">4</span> Whiter Teeth that are Hard to Stain</h3>\r\nOne of the most common reasons people opt for porcelain veneers is that they have stained teeth. Teeth whitening can take weeks and isn’t always an option, but a veneer can be a great alternative. A single visit to the dentist can provide you with a sparkly, white smile.\r\n\r\nBest of all, the material we use for our veneers has more stain resistance than your actual teeth. That means that, with proper oral care like brushing your teeth, your smile will stay brighter for longer.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">5</span> Low Pain and a Comfortable Atmosphere</h3>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"smiling-woman-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4098 img-circle\" /></a></div>\r\nAt Blevins Dentistry, we strive to make every patient feel welcome and comfortable. We know that a visit to the dentist office can be scary for some people, so we do our best to make it an enjoyable experience. We listen to your needs, investigate the situation in your mouth, and work with you to determine the best path forward.\r\n\r\nWe make the process of getting porcelain veneers as painless as possible. Little to no aesthetic is required, but we treat each patient according to the needs of the situation. \r\n\r\nOnce you have your new veneers, your new smile might feel a bit funny, but you shouldn’t experience pain. Some patients do experience temperature sensitivity, but this does not last for long. Mostly, however, you’ll just be excited to show off your new smile!\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Contact us for Your Consultation</h3>\r\nIf you think porcelain veneers might be right for you and you live in or near Mullins, South Carolina, then <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact\">contact us</a> today to schedule your consultation. \r\n\r\nDr. Blevins enjoys meeting with patients, both old and new, and will work with you to determine the best path forward. Having a great smile is important for your health and confidence, and we’ll ensure you are happy with the results.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<small>Sources: <a href=\"http://www.colgate.com/en/us/oc/oral-health/cosmetic-dentistry/veneers/article/how-porcelain-dental-veneers-can-rebuild-your-smile-0614\" target=\"_blank\">How Porcelain Dental Veneers Can Rebuild Your Smile</a></small>','The Top 5 Benefits of Porcelain Veneers from Dr. Blevins','','publish','open','open','','the-top-5-benefits-of-porcelain-veneers-from-dr-blevins','','','2016-11-03 17:40:59','2016-11-03 17:40:59','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4341',0,'post','',0),(4342,1001007,'2016-10-03 16:30:12','2016-10-03 16:30:12','','porcelain_durathin_veneer-web-size','','inherit','open','closed','','porcelain_durathin_veneer-web-size','','','2016-10-03 16:30:12','2016-10-03 16:30:12','',4341,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/porcelain_DURAthin_veneer-web-size.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4346,1001007,'2016-10-18 19:16:23','2016-10-18 19:16:23','','iwp_log_58067507d6d55','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_58067507d6d55','','','2016-10-18 19:16:23','2016-10-18 19:16:23','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_58067507d6d55/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4347,1001007,'2016-10-18 19:21:42','2016-10-18 19:21:42','','iwp_log_5806764662e90','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5806764662e90','','','2016-10-18 19:21:42','2016-10-18 19:21:42','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5806764662e90/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4350,1001007,'2016-10-28 16:29:34','2016-10-28 16:29:34','','iwp_log_58137cee9f27a','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_58137cee9f27a','','','2016-10-28 16:29:34','2016-10-28 16:29:34','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_58137cee9f27a/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4351,1001007,'2016-10-28 16:29:34','2016-10-28 16:29:34','','iwp_log_58137ceeaa193','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_58137ceeaa193','','','2016-10-28 16:29:34','2016-10-28 16:29:34','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_58137ceeaa193/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4352,1001007,'2016-10-28 16:29:52','2016-10-28 16:29:52','','iwp_log_58137d00801a0','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_58137d00801a0','','','2016-10-28 16:29:52','2016-10-28 16:29:52','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_58137d00801a0/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4353,1001007,'2016-10-28 16:39:59','2016-10-28 16:39:59','<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-7\">\r\n    <div class=\"video-container\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Du1krP6hBrA\" data-lity>\r\n          <span class=\"fa-stack fa-2x\">\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n            <i class=\"fa fa-play fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n          </span>\r\n          <div class=\"shader\"></div>\r\n          <img src=\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/Du1krP6hBrA/maxresdefault.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-4192\" />\r\n        </a>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-5\">\r\n    <p class=\"lead\">If you are missing teeth, you’ve undoubtedly explored different options for replacing them. Should you get dentures, a bridge, dental implants, or something else?</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, we’ll focus on dental implants, discussing the pros and cons to give you the information you need to help make a decision about replacing your missing tooth/teeth. As always, if you have any questions, you’re welcome to <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">contact us</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>What are Dental Implants?</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p><a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants\">Dental implants</a> are titanium posts that are inserted through your gums into your jawbone. They replace the roots of your natural teeth, and provide an anchor upon which replacement teeth are placed. According to the <a href=\"http://www.mouthhealthy.org/en/az-topics/i/implants\" target=\"_blank\">American Dental Association</a>, \"the development and use of implants is one of the biggest advances in dentistry in the past 40 years.\"</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/implant-square2-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/implant-square2-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"implant-square2\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4127 img-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"clear:none;\">Pros of Dental Implants</h3>\r\n<p><strong>They provide a permanent solution:</strong>\r\nMany people opt for dental implants because they are permanent. Once the titanium post is fused to your jawbone, it won’t move for a long time. That means you never have to remove the implant to clean it, like dentures. It won’t get lost and will be very difficult to break. You won’t need a replacement implant any time soon, if ever.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>They won’t slip or move:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Because implants fuse to your jawbone, they are very secure. Eating with <a href=\"http://www.mouthhealthy.org/en/az-topics/d/dentures\" target=\"_blank\">dentures</a> or bridges can be frustrating. They can slip and pinch your gums when eating or speaking. Dentures can fall out at embarrassing times. But not implants; they hold fast to the jawbone and provide a much more comfortable experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>They look and feel natural:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dental implants are designed and shaped to look just like your natural teeth. Even the color will match the shade of your teeth, providing a natural look and a smile you can be proud of.</p> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>They can be treated just like natural teeth:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Not only do implants look natural, you can treat and clean them just like your natural teeth. If you can eat something with your natural teeth, you can eat it with implants. Caring and cleaning for your implants requires brushing and flossing, just like your natural teeth. In fact, dental implants can seem so natural you might even forget it’s actually a fake tooth!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>They support healthy bone structure:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you lose a tooth, your jawbone will slowly start to shrink. Since the bone no longer needs to support the roots, it simply fades. When this happens, the gums also begin to recede. Dentures cannot help prevent this because the fake teeth merely sit on top of the gums, but dental implants are different. The titanium posts act as roots for the teeth, giving the jawbone something to grab hold of and a reason to stay strong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>They stand on their own:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Replacement solutions like <a href=\"http://www.mouthhealthy.org/en/az-topics/b/bridges\" target=\"_blank\">dental bridges</a> require nearby teeth. A fake tooth is placed in between your natural teeth to “bridge” the gap, but it is dependent on those natural teeth to stay in place. Because dental implants are held fast by the titanium posts, the nearby teeth do not need adjustments. In fact, dental implants can replace every tooth in your mouth if that is your requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Cons of Dental Implants</h3>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>The Cost:</strong>\r\n    <p>Many people shy away from dental implants because of the cost. However, when you consider the permanent nature of implants, they actually provide tremendous value. It’s often cheaper and less stressful to get one solution that lasts for decades instead of a solution that needs replacing or updating every couple of years.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-implant-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/dental-implant-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"dental-implant-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4129 img-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>They take time:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Placing dental implants is a multi-step process. First, we need to assess your situation to determine if you are a good candidate for dental implants. Then, we place the titanium posts into your jawbone and need to provide time for the bone to properly fuse to your implants. This can sometimes take several months. Fortunately, we can provide a temporary fake tooth or teeth so you don’t have to walk around with nothing but titanium posts. Once the titanium posts are secure, we apply the permanent replacement tooth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>They require strong bone structure:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Because implants require strong bone structure, some patients may require <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/bone-grafting/\" target=\"_blank\">bone grafting</a>. This process restores the strength of your jawbone, but requires 3 months time to heal before implants can be placed.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"blevins-team-square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4318 img-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3 style=\"clear:none;\">What now?</h3>\r\n    <p>If you’d like to learn more about dental implants, or if you’re ready to improve your smile, then <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">contact us at our Mullins, SC dental office</a> and schedule a consultation.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Dr. Blevins is one of South Carolina’s most accomplished dentists and has extensive experience providing patients with implants. He is passionate about restoring people’s smiles and will analyze your specific needs to identify the best solution.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<p><small>Sources<br />\r\n• <a href=\"http://www.colgate.com/en/us/oc/oral-health/cosmetic-dentistry/implants/article/how-dental-implants-can-save-your-smile-0415\" target=\"_blank\">How dental implants can save your smile</a><br />\r\n• <a href=\"http://www.colgate.com/en/us/oc/oral-health/cosmetic-dentistry/implants/article/what-are-dental-implants\" target=\"_blank\">What are dental implants?</a><br />\r\n• <a href=\"http://www.thedentalguide.net/pros-cons-dental-implants/\" target=\"_blank\">The Dental Guide - Pros and Cons of implants</a></small></p>','What are the Pros and Cons of Dental Implants?','','publish','open','open','','what-are-the-pros-and-cons-of-dental-implants','','','2017-09-27 17:53:10','2017-09-27 17:53:10','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4353',0,'post','',0),(4354,1001007,'2016-10-28 16:38:29','2016-10-28 16:38:29','','implant-feature-image','','inherit','open','closed','','implant-feature-image','','','2016-10-28 16:38:29','2016-10-28 16:38:29','',4353,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/implant-feature-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4355,1001007,'2016-10-31 19:08:14','2016-10-31 19:08:14','','iwp_log_5817969e533f2','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5817969e533f2','','','2016-10-31 19:08:14','2016-10-31 19:08:14','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5817969e533f2/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4356,1001007,'2016-10-31 19:08:51','2016-10-31 19:08:51','','slide-use-it-or-lose-it','','inherit','open','closed','','slide-use-it-or-lose-it','','','2016-10-31 19:08:51','2016-10-31 19:08:51','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/slide-use-it-or-lose-it.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4357,1001007,'2016-10-31 19:13:33','2016-10-31 19:13:33','','slide-use-it-or-lose-it','','inherit','open','closed','','slide-use-it-or-lose-it-2','','','2016-10-31 19:13:33','2016-10-31 19:13:33','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/slide-use-it-or-lose-it-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4358,1001007,'2016-10-31 19:17:37','2016-10-31 19:17:37','','dental-exam-banner','','inherit','open','closed','','dental-exam-banner','','','2016-10-31 19:17:37','2016-10-31 19:17:37','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dental-exam-banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4359,1001007,'2016-11-03 17:15:28','2016-11-03 17:15:28','','iwp_log_581b70b06a879','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_581b70b06a879','','','2016-11-03 17:15:28',