one of your baby teeth became loose? You knew that, within a few days, you’d lose the tooth and get a visit from the tooth fairy!\r\n\r\nThe emotions you felt as a child were probably just as strong as the frustration and annoyance you feel as an adult when you realize one of your teeth is loose or cracked. \r\n\r\nAs an adult, you want your teeth to last a lifetime. They are vital to your eating and speaking-- two things that adults need to do multiple times each day!\r\n\r\nIf you have loose or cracking teeth, your next step is very simple, but important: You need to visit a dentist. Both loose and cracked teeth can have different causes, and the earlier you see a dentist, the more likely it is that you can save your teeth. \r\n\r\nSometimes a tooth needs to be removed, in which case it can be replaced by an <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dental-implants/\">implant</a>. Even in those cases, visiting the dentist early could prevent the loss of other teeth in the future. \r\n\r\nIn this article, we’ll take a look at the different causes of loose and cracked teeth to help you understand what you’ll need to do.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Cause <span class=\"num\">1</span> Malocclusion</h3>\r\nMalocclusion is a fancy word for a bad bite. There are many types of malocclusions, including:\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Underbite</li>\r\n	<li>Overbite</li>\r\n	<li>Overcrowded teeth</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Crossbite</li>\r\n	<li>Openbite</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nWhatever the cause, malocclusions occur when your teeth do not fit together properly. Although you may not experience discomfort, extra pressure is being applied to specific teeth every time you bite down or chew. This extra pressure over time can cause cracked or broken teeth and can also lead to severe jaw pain. \r\n\r\nIf you have a bad bite and it has already caused a tooth to crack or become loose, it’s important to get your bite corrected. In many cases, your dentist can help correct malocclusion, or depending on the severity of the bite issue, they may refer you to an orthodontist. Not only that, but it’s also important to get the cracked tooth repaired. Cracked teeth can be painful or sensitive to temperature changes, and you shouldn’t have to live with that.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/gum-disease-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4062 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Cause <span class=\"num\">2</span> Gum Disease</h3>\r\n    Loose teeth are often caused by gum disease, which comes in two stages: gingivitis and periodontitis. \r\n\r\n    Gingivitis is the earlier stage of gum disease. It is caused by plaque and calculus buildup on the teeth, which then cause gum inflammation. Periodontitis is more advanced, and the disease infects the gum tissue more seriously. As the plaque and calculus grow beneath the gums, they create pockets of space and cause infection and loss of the supporting bone tissue.\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nAs these pockets grow, the teeth become loose. If your teeth have become loose, then it’s important to see a dentist right away. Periodontitis can only be treated by a professional dentist; you won’t be able to fight it on your own. \r\n\r\nIf you decide to ignore the loose teeth, you might actually lose the teeth. Not only that, but gum disease can also cause the following issues:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Persistent bad breath or a bad taste in your mouth</li>\r\n	<li>Overly sensitive teeth to cold and hot</li>\r\n	<li>Gums can become swollen, tender, or bleed often</li>\r\n	<li>The bacteria from your gums can get into your bloodstream, which can then travel to the arteries in the heart and cause them to harden. This can then decrease or even block blood flow to the rest of the body, increasing the risk of heart attack or stroke</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Cause <span class=\"num\">3</span> Osteoporosis</h3>\r\nOsteoporosis is a condition that affects both men and women. It causes the bones throughout the body to become less dense and more prone to fracture. When the density of the jawbone that supports your teeth begins to drop, the teeth can become loose. In fact, women with osteoporosis are three times more likely to experience tooth loss than women without it.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Cause <span class=\"num\">4</span> Accidents</h3>\r\nAccidents are a common cause of loose and cracked teeth. Whether you’ve fallen, been hit, or just gotten unlucky, it’s important to treat accidents like a dental emergency. The quicker you visit the dentist, the more likely it is that you can save your teeth. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3><span class=\"num\">?</span> What to do</h3>\r\n    As you can see, most of the causes for loose or cracked teeth cannot be treated at home. While things like brushing and flossing can help prevent teeth from becoming loose, curing the problem often requires professional intervention. \r\n\r\n    While you wait for your dentist appointment, these tips are also important to remember:\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/flossing-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/flossing-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4406 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Avoid playing with your loose tooth - it can be tempting to push loose teeth with your tongue, but this will only make things worse.</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid sticky and crunchy foods. Sticky candies, for instance, can instantly pull your loose tooth out. Crunchy ones can create bigger cracks or cause loose teeth to fall out.</li>\r\n	<li>Continue cleaning your teeth, but do so very gently. Don’t brush or floss with much force; you don’t want to expedite the problem.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4318 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3><span class=\"num\"><i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i></span> Where to go</h3>\r\n    As you can tell, people with loose or cracking teeth should get to the dentist as soon as possible. If you’re in the Mullins, South Carolina area, then there are many <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/11-reasons-to-choose-blevins-dentistry-in-mullins-sc/\">reasons why Blevins Dentistry is the right choice</a> for you. \r\n\r\n    We have patients who drive as far as 50 miles to experience the Blevins Dentistry difference. We know we can help you feel comfortable and care for your loose or cracked teeth.\r\n\r\n    With years of experience and an excellent team, we won’t just treat the symptoms; we will identify and treat the cause. <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/contact/\">Contact us</a> today to schedule an appointment...we’d love to meet you.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<small>Sources:<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.colgate.com/en/us/oc/oral-health/conditions/dental-emergencies-and-sports-safety/article/fractured-and-broken-teeth\" target=\"_blank\">Fractured and Broken Teeth</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.colgate.com/en/us/oc/oral-health/life-stages/adult-oral-care/article/the-many-causes-of-loose-teeth-0214\" target=\"_blank\">The Many Causes of Loose Teeth</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.colgate.com/en/us/oc/oral-health/conditions/cracked-tooth-syndrome/article/what-to-do-if-you-have-a-cracked-molar-0613\" target=\"_blank\">What to do if you have a cracked molar</a></small>','Loose or Cracking Teeth as an Adult? Here\'s What to Do','','publish','open','open','','loose-or-cracking-teeth-as-an-adult-heres-what-to-do','','\nhttp://www.blevinsdentistry.com/11-reasons-to-choose-blevins-dentistry-in-mullins-sc/','2017-04-20 19:50:12','2017-04-20 19:50:12','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4560',0,'post','',0),(4561,1001007,'2017-04-20 19:44:01','2017-04-20 19:44:01','','shutterstock_613110224','','inherit','open','closed','','shutterstock_613110224','','','2017-04-20 19:44:01','2017-04-20 19:44:01','',4560,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/shutterstock_613110224.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4564,1001007,'2017-05-02 16:05:02','2017-05-02 16:05:02','','iwp_log_5908ae2e92079','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5908ae2e92079','','','2017-05-02 16:05:02','2017-05-02 16:05:02','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5908ae2e92079/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4565,1001007,'2017-05-02 16:06:01','2017-05-02 16:06:01','','iwp_log_5908ae6904fbc','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5908ae6904fbc','','','2017-05-02 16:06:01','2017-05-02 16:06:01','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5908ae6904fbc/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4567,1001007,'2017-05-12 16:51:55','2017-05-12 16:51:55','','iwp_log_5915e82bd2738','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5915e82bd2738','','','2017-05-12 16:51:55','2017-05-12 16:51:55','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5915e82bd2738/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4568,1001007,'2017-05-12 16:51:55','2017-05-12 16:51:55','','iwp_log_5915e82bf2d85','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5915e82bf2d85','','','2017-05-12 16:51:55','2017-05-12 16:51:55','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5915e82bf2d85/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4569,1001007,'2017-05-12 16:51:56','2017-05-12 16:51:56','','iwp_log_5915e82c0d030','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5915e82c0d030','','','2017-05-12 16:51:56','2017-05-12 16:51:56','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5915e82c0d030/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4570,1001007,'2017-05-12 16:52:23','2017-05-12 16:52:23','','iwp_log_5915e847486da','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5915e847486da','','','2017-05-12 16:52:23','2017-05-12 16:52:23','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5915e847486da/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4571,1001007,'2017-05-18 16:38:06','2017-05-18 16:38:06','','iwp_log_591dcdee73e81','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_591dcdee73e81','','','2017-05-18 16:38:06','2017-05-18 16:38:06','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_591dcdee73e81/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4573,1001007,'2017-05-18 19:12:27','2017-05-18 19:12:27','','slide-6','','inherit','open','closed','','slide-6','','','2017-05-18 19:12:27','2017-05-18 19:12:27','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/slide-6.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4576,1001007,'2017-05-24 21:07:52','2017-05-24 21:07:52','','iwp_log_5925f628d2cab','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5925f628d2cab','','','2017-05-24 21:07:52','2017-05-24 21:07:52','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5925f628d2cab/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4577,1001007,'2017-05-30 14:03:11','2017-05-30 14:03:11','','iwp_log_592d7b9fd9619','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_592d7b9fd9619','','','2017-05-30 14:03:11','2017-05-30 14:03:11','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_592d7b9fd9619/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4578,1001007,'2017-05-30 14:10:15','2017-05-30 14:10:15','As a cosmetic dentistry practice, our real value to patients is being able to give them the smile of their dreams, provide incredible service, and ultimately boost their self-esteem. \r\n\r\nThat’s the end goal. Cosmetic dentistry is the “tool” we use to improve our patients’ lives. \r\n\r\nSpeaking of goals…\r\n\r\nOne of the most common things we hear from patients when they visit us for a consultation is, “How can I improve the appearance of my front teeth when I smile?”\r\n\r\nThat is the goal that many patients are looking to accomplish. \r\n\r\nThis is obviously a broad question because every patient may have a different issue they are wanting to improve upon. Some patients simply want to whiten their teeth, while others may be interested in straightening their teeth, fixing gaps, etc. \r\n\r\nIn this blog post, we’re going to cover four common treatment options that we use at Blevins Dentistry to help patients improve the appearance of their front teeth and give them a smile they are looking for.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Bonding</h3>\r\n\r\nDental bonding is a relatively simple procedure that is used to fix minor cracks or chips in teeth. Here are a few benefits of dental bonding:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>It is an outpatient procedure that typically does not require any sedation.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Bonding is a minimally-invasive procedure that can be done in our office and completed in just a few minutes.</li>\r\n	<li>For some patients with only minor issues (such as a cracked front tooth due to minor trauma) bonding may be a perfect, simple, and affordable solution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nWhile bonding can be a great solution to improve the appearance of your front teeth, it’s important to note that it is best suited for situations where a minimal amount of work needs to be done. \r\n\r\nIf you have significant issues that need to be addressed, bonding alone probably isn’t the best option for you. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Teeth Whitening</h3>\r\n\r\n    Professional, in-office teeth whitening is a very common procedure at Blevins Dentistry. While there are many OTC whitening solutions, there is nothing that works as well as professional whitening. \r\n\r\n    At Blevins Dentistry, we use Boost Whitening as our professional whitening solution. Here are just a few benefits of Boost Whitening:\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n	<li>Boost is chemically activated, meaning you will not be exposed to hot, annoying lights during your whitening procedure.</li>\r\n	<li>Dr. Blevins will apply the exact amount of whitening required to achieve the look you want; no more and no less.</li>\r\n	<li>You can expect that our in-office Boost whitening system will make your teeth several shades whiter in less than an hour.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/whitening-square.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/whitening-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4102 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nIn-office whitening from Blevins Dentistry is best suited for patients who have mild to moderate “yellow or brown teeth” due to smoking, drinking dark beverages, and things of that nature. \r\n\r\nIf you like the general look and shape of your teeth, but they’re just a little too dingy, then professional whitening may be the perfect option for you. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Dental Crowns</h3>\r\n\r\nCrowns are typically used to replace front teeth that have been lost or taken out due to decay or damage. In fact, dental crowns are often used in conjunction with a dental implant restoration. \r\n\r\nIn addition to single crowns, a bridge (which is just a series of crowns) may also be used as part of a dental implant restoration. \r\n\r\nHere are a few benefits of dental crowns:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dental crowns are “custom fit” to your mouth. We do this by taking a digital impression of your teeth and using CEREC to fabricate your crowns in our office on the same day.</li> \r\n	<li>A dental crown (or multiple crowns) with look like your natural teeth. At Blevins Dentistry, we use porcelain crowns, as metal crowns tend to “fade” over time and give your entire tooth a dull, metallic, gray appearance. </li>\r\n	<li>If you receive crowns on your front teeth, you’ll not only look better, but also have more functionality.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nThe best part? With CEREC technology available at Blevins Dentistry, we can now make and place your dental crowns in a single visit! \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/veneers-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-4112 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>Porcelain Veneers</h3>\r\n\r\n    If you are truly looking for your dream smile and want your front teeth to look absolutely flawless, then porcelain veneers are exactly what you’re looking for. \r\n\r\n    Just like with dental crowns, we are able to fabricate porcelain veneers in our office (using CEREC technology), which means you can truly have your dream smile in a single dental visit. \r\n\r\n    Pretty incredible, right?\r\n\r\n    Here are a few reasons why porcelain veneers are the “bees knees” when it comes to improving the appearance of your front teeth:\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Porcelain veneers are customizable. When you meet with Dr. Blevins, he will work with you to determine the perfect size, shape, and color to give you a smile that looks perfect, and yet still retains a natural look.</li> \r\n	<li>Porcelain veneers typically will last 10 or more years with proper care and maintenance. Dr. Blevins will teach you everything you need to know regarding proper care for your new veneers.</li>\r\n	<li>Veneers can fix teeth that are severely misshapen or teeth that are cracked, chipped, stained, broken, etc...they are a truly comprehensive solution to anyone who is looking to achieve beautiful front teeth!</li>\r\n	<li>Veneers are the cream of the crop when it comes to cosmetic dentistry and restoring your smile; it’s a great option for just about anyone.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to learn more about porcelain veneers, visit the link below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/single-visit-veneers\">http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/single-visit-veneers</a>\r\n\r\nAlso, if you would like to learn more about CEREC technology and how we are able to craft crowns and veneers in our office using this technology, read the article below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/veneers-in-a-day-its-possible-with-cerec-technology\">http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/veneers-in-a-day-its-possible-with-cerec-technology</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    <h3>So, what’s the next step to improving the appearance of your front teeth?</h3>\r\n\r\n    If you are within driving distance of Mullins, SC (many patients come see us from 50+ miles away), then we encourage you to give our office a call and schedule your cosmetic dentistry consultation. \r\n\r\n    You’ll be able to meet Dr. Blevins and get a feel for what option may be best suited to improve the appearance of your front teeth. We look forward to meeting you soon!\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <a href=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/blevins-team-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-4318 rounded-circle\" /></a>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','How to Improve the Appearance of Your Front Teeth','','publish','open','open','','how-to-improve-the-appearance-of-your-front-teeth','','\nhttp://www.blevinsdentistry.com/veneers-in-a-day-its-possible-with-cerec-technology','2017-05-30 14:19:28','2017-05-30 14:19:28','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4578',0,'post','',0),(4579,1001007,'2017-05-30 14:09:57','2017-05-30 14:09:57','','feature-image-straight-teeth','','inherit','open','closed','','feature-image-straight-teeth-2','','','2017-05-30 14:09:57','2017-05-30 14:09:57','',4578,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/feature-image-straight-teeth.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4583,1001007,'2017-07-06 19:49:58','2017-07-06 19:49:58','','iwp_log_595e9466de87d','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_595e9466de87d','','','2017-07-06 19:49:58','2017-07-06 19:49:58','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_595e9466de87d/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4584,1001007,'2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','','iwp_log_595e953ea7d37','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_595e953ea7d37','','','2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_595e953ea7d37/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4585,1001007,'2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','','iwp_log_595e953ec036d','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_595e953ec036d','','','2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_595e953ec036d/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4586,1001007,'2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','','iwp_log_595e953ed184d','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_595e953ed184d','','','2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_595e953ed184d/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4587,1001007,'2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','','iwp_log_595e953ee0acf','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_595e953ee0acf','','','2017-07-06 19:53:34','2017-07-06 19:53:34','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_595e953ee0acf/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4