sed','closed','','iwp_log_5a624f42f3004','','','2018-01-19 20:04:18','2018-01-19 20:04:18','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5a624f42f3004/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4736,1001007,'2018-01-23 20:08:03','2018-01-23 20:08:03','','iwp_log_5a67962381a43','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5a67962381a43','','','2018-01-23 20:08:03','2018-01-23 20:08:03','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5a67962381a43/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4737,1001007,'2018-01-23 20:08:26','2018-01-23 20:08:26','','iwp_log_5a67963a5095d','','publish','closed','closed','','iwp_log_5a67963a5095d','','','2018-01-23 20:08:26','2018-01-23 20:08:26','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/iwp_log_5a67963a5095d/',0,'iwp_log','',0),(4738,1001007,'2018-01-23 20:17:37','2018-01-23 20:17:37','We’ve all seen that person with a perfect smile. \r\n\r\nWhen you’re having a conversation with them or even in the same room with them, you tend to keep your mouth closed because you don’t want anyone comparing your smile to that one!\r\n\r\nNow, let me ask you a question…\r\n\r\nWhat if you didn’t feel like you had to “smile with your mouth closed?”\r\n\r\nWhat if you could open your mouth and smile big knowing that your smile looks just as great as anyone else’s in the room?\r\n\r\nThat’s exactly what a smile makeover from Dr. Todd Blevins can do for you!\r\n\r\nBut we’re going to dive a little deeper. In this article I’m going to share with you 3 scenarios where a smile makeover can significantly improve your quality of life. \r\n\r\nRemember, when you truly find your personal “why,” you’ll be much more motivated to stop hesitating and take the next step to making a change.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to learn more about the smile makeover service we offer at Blevins Dentistry (and why patients travel from all over South Carolina to see Dr. Blevins) visit our page on smile makeovers here:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.blevinsdentistry.com/smile-makeovers\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Smile Makeovers <i class=\"fa fa-angle-right\"></i></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">1</span> A smile makeover before a major life event</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    It’s not uncommon for a bride or a groom to want to drop some weight before a wedding. In fact, I bet you’ve had a friend or family member who tried desperately to shed a few pounds before their big day.\r\n\r\n    Why do they want to do this? Why do they work so hard to look better before the big day?\r\n\r\n    It’s primarily for two reasons:\r\n\r\n    <strong>A.</strong> They want to look great in photos and videos\r\n    <strong>B.</strong> They want to increase their confidence and self-esteem so they can enjoy the day instead of worrying about what they look like\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/smiling-woman-square-1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4098\" />\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nBut this isn’t just about weddings...far from it. There are many major events that come along in life where you might want to consider a smile makeover beforehand. \r\n\r\nHere are a few:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You’re moving to a new city (and thus meeting new friends) and you want to make a great first impression.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>You’ve just landed a new job (or you are looking for a new job) and you want to make a great first impression for your new employer or client.</li> \r\n\r\n	<li>You have a class or family reunion coming up and you know you’ll see people you haven’t seen in a long time (and you want to look good, nothing wrong with that).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nThe list goes on and on I’m sure (those are just three reasons I’ve heard from my patients). So do you have a major life event coming up and you want to smile confidently?\r\n\r\nWant to walk into the room with a newfound level of confidence and self-esteem? A smile makeover may be just what you need.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">2</span> A smile makeover before meeting someone special</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n    <img src=\"http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/doctor-patient-square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-4037\" />\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n    Whether you’re looking or not, you just never know when you might find that special someone who turns your world upside down (in a good way!). \r\n\r\n    Let’s say you’re a 53-year-old woman (or any other age or gender really) and you’re looking to get back out there and find someone special. You’ve always taken care of yourself, but you’re a little self-conscious about your crooked smile. \r\n\r\n    Even if your smile isn’t really that bad, the loss of self-esteem that it gives can turn into a much bigger problem.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\nYou could continue to look in the mirror every day, wondering if your smile is holding you back and keeping you from meeting someone great OR you can do something about it…improve your overall appearance, health, wellness and total happiness with a smile makeover. \r\n\r\nWhich decision will you make? If you’d like to learn more about Dr. Blevins and the smiles he creates for his patients at Blevins Dentistry, click the link below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins/\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Dr. Blevins <i class=\"fa fa-angle-right\"></i></a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"num\">3</span> Getting a smile makeover because, well, you’ve waited too long and now is the time!</h3>\r\n\r\nWhile specific life events sometimes trigger the want or need for a smile makeover, in many cases patients come to Blevins Dentistry because they’ve been thinking about it for years, and in their words, “Now is just the right time to do this.”\r\n\r\nThat’s great!\r\n\r\nWe love it when patients call our office and tell us they are interested in a smile makeover because they’ve put other people first for so many years, and now it’s time to treat themselves to something nice.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>So what is the next step?</h3>\r\n\r\nWe hope this article has shown you that a smile makeover really is worth it no matter the reason for wanting one.\r\n\r\nAt Blevins Dentistry, Dr. Todd Blevins utilizes a variety of cosmetic and restorative procedures to provide patients with their dream smile. The services typically used to create a dream smile are some combination of:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dental crowns or bridges</li>\r\n	<li>Dental implants</li>\r\n	<li>Cosmetic bonding</li>\r\n	<li>Teeth whitening</li> \r\n	<li>Veneers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nAnd more. <strong>Our #1 priority is listening to you so that we can understand your goals, what you are looking to achieve with your smile, and turn that vision into a reality.</strong>\r\n\r\nSo what are you waiting for? Give our Mullins, SC dental practice a call today to schedule your smile makeover consultation.','Are Smile Makeovers Really Worth It? 3 Real-life Scenarios Where Smile Makeovers Can Improve Your Quality of Life','','publish','open','open','','are-smile-makeovers-really-worth-it-3-real-life-scenarios-where-smile-makeovers-can-improve-your-quality-of-life','','','2018-01-23 20:20:39','2018-01-23 20:20:39','',0,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/?p=4738',0,'post','',0),(4739,1001007,'2018-01-23 20:17:29','2018-01-23 20:17:29','','feature-image-straightened-teeth','','inherit','open','closed','','feature-image-straightened-teeth','','','2018-01-23 20:17:29','2018-01-23 20:17:29','',4738,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/feature-image-straightened-teeth.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(4740,1001007,'2018-01-23 20:18:57','2018-01-23 20:18:57','We’ve all seen that person with a perfect smile. \n\nWhen you’re having a conversation with them or even in the same room with them, you tend to keep your mouth closed because you don’t want anyone comparing your smile to that one!\n\nNow, let me ask you a question…\n\nWhat if you didn’t feel like you had to “smile with your mouth closed?”\n\nWhat if you could open your mouth and smile big knowing that your smile looks just as great as anyone else’s in the room?\n\nThat’s exactly what a smile makeover from Dr. Todd Blevins can do for you!\n\nBut we’re going to dive a little deeper. In this article I’m going to share with you 3 scenarios where a smile makeover can significantly improve your quality of life. \n\nRemember, when you truly find your personal “why,” you’ll be much more motivated to stop hesitating and take the next step to making a change.\n\nIf you would like to learn more about the smile makeover service we offer at Blevins Dentistry (and why patients travel from all over South Carolina to see Dr. Blevins) visit our page on smile makeovers here:\n\n<a href=\"https://www.blevinsdentistry.com/smile-makeovers\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Smile Makeovers <i class=\"fa fa-angle-right\"></i></a>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h3><span class=\"num\">1</span> A smile makeover before a major life event</h3>\n\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\n  <div class=\"col-lg-8\">\n    It’s not uncommon for a bride or a groom to want to drop some weight before a wedding. In fact, I bet you’ve had a friend or family member who tried desperately to shed a few pounds before their big day.\n\n    Why do they want to do this? Why do they work so hard to look better before the big day?\n\n    It’s primarily for two reasons:\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\n    \n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<strong>A.</strong> They want to look great in photos and videos\n<strong>B.</strong> They want to increase their confidence and self-esteem so they can enjoy the day instead of worrying about what they look like\n\nBut this isn’t just about weddings...far from it. There are many major events that come along in life where you might want to consider a smile makeover beforehand. \n\nHere are a few:\n\n<ul>\n	<li>You’re moving to a new city (and thus meeting new friends) and you want to make a great first impression.</li>\n\n	<li>You’ve just landed a new job (or you are looking for a new job) and you want to make a great first impression for your new employer or client.</li> \n\n	<li>You have a class or family reunion coming up and you know you’ll see people you haven’t seen in a long time (and you want to look good, nothing wrong with that).</li>\n</ul>\n\nThe list goes on and on I’m sure (those are just three reasons I’ve heard from my patients). So do you have a major life event coming up and you want to smile confidently?\n\nWant to walk into the room with a newfound level of confidence and self-esteem? A smile makeover may be just what you need.\n\n<hr />\n\n<h3><span class=\"num\">2</span> A smile makeover before meeting someone special</h3>\n\nWhether you’re looking or not, you just never know when you might find that special someone who turns your world upside down (in a good way!). \n\nLet’s say you’re a 53-year-old woman (or any other age or gender really) and you’re looking to get back out there and find someone special. You’ve always taken care of yourself, but you’re a little self-conscious about your crooked smile. \n\nEven if your smile isn’t really that bad, the loss of self-esteem that it gives can turn into a much bigger problem. \n\nYou could continue to look in the mirror every day, wondering if your smile is holding you back and keeping you from meeting someone great OR you can do something about it…improve your overall appearance, health, wellness and total happiness with a smile makeover. \n\nWhich decision will you make? If you’d like to learn more about Dr. Blevins and the smiles he creates for his patients at Blevins Dentistry, click the link below:\n\n<a href=\"https://www.blevinsdentistry.com/dr-blevins/\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Dr. Blevins <i class=\"fa fa-angle-right\"></i></a>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h3><span class=\"num\">3</span> Getting a smile makeover because, well, you’ve waited too long and now is the time!</h3>\n\nWhile specific life events sometimes trigger the want or need for a smile makeover, in many cases patients come to Blevins Dentistry because they’ve been thinking about it for years, and in their words, “Now is just the right time to do this.”\n\nThat’s great!\n\nWe love it when patients call our office and tell us they are interested in a smile makeover because they’ve put other people first for so many years, and now it’s time to treat themselves to something nice.\n\n<hr />\n\n<h3>So what is the next step?</h3>\n\nWe hope this article has shown you that a smile makeover really is worth it no matter the reason for wanting one.\n\nAt Blevins Dentistry, Dr. Todd Blevins utilizes a variety of cosmetic and restorative procedures to provide patients with their dream smile. The services typically used to create a dream smile are some combination of:\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dental crowns or bridges</li>\n	<li>Dental implants</li>\n	<li>Cosmetic bonding</li>\n	<li>Teeth whitening</li> \n	<li>Veneers</li>\n</ul>\n\nAnd more. <strong>Our #1 priority is listening to you so that we can understand your goals, what you are looking to achieve with your smile, and turn that vision into a reality.</strong>\n\nSo what are you waiting for? Give our Mullins, SC dental practice a call today to schedule your smile makeover consultation.','Are Smile Makeovers Really Worth It? 3 Real-life Scenarios Where Smile Makeovers Can Improve Your Quality of Life','','inherit','closed','closed','','4738-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-23 20:18:57','2018-01-23 20:18:57','',4738,'http://www.blevinsdentistry.com/4738-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(4741,1001007,'2018-02-01 16:31:29','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2018-02-01 16:31:29','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'htt